<Requirements version="3" hierarchy="LLR">
  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.1 Explore Maze -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration State Machine</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.1.4</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INIT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a top-level mission control state machine with at least the states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED} and deterministic transitions between them, such that:
(1) In the IDLE state, the state machine shall wait for receipt of an INIT_COMPLETED indication from the initialization module and then transition to EXPLORE.
(2) In the EXPLORE state, the state machine shall periodically request frontier targets from the frontier-generation module, request paths to the selected target from the path planner, and command the motion controller to execute the resulting motion primitives until either exploration completion or an exploration timeout event is received.
(3) In the RETURN_TO_START state, the state machine shall invoke the return-to-start service to compute a path to the start cell and shall command the motion controller to execute that path until the start cell is reached or a planning failure is reported.
(4) In the SECOND_RUN state, the state machine shall invoke the second-run planning service to compute the fastest path from the start cell to the goal region, shall command the motion controller to execute that path, and shall wait for receipt of a second-run status (success or failure).
(5) In the COMPLETED state, the state machine shall cease issuing new motion commands and maintain the final second-run status for external reporting.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Start Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INIT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall cause the mission control state machine to enter the EXPLORE state automatically when, within the periodic control loop, the initialization module has signaled INIT_COMPLETED and the sensor abstraction layer has provided at least one valid set of ultrasonic and infrared measurements.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Stop Condition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.6</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall terminate the EXPLORE state and initiate RETURN_TO_START when either:
(1) the map completeness condition defined by the grid map module indicates that no cell or inter-cell wall segment remains in the UNKNOWN state, or
(2) the global exploration time limit defined in the time-limit requirement has been reached,
whichever condition is signaled first by the corresponding modules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier-Based Exploration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-based exploration strategy in the EXPLORE state such that the mission control state machine selects as navigation targets cells that are currently classified as UNKNOWN but are adjacent (in the 4-neighborhood) to at least one FREE cell in the internal grid map and requests paths to these targets from the path planner.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Frontier Generation Module</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a frontier-generation module that, upon request from the mission control state machine or planner, returns the set of all cells whose state is UNKNOWN and that are 4-neighbors of at least one FREE cell in the grid map, and shall recompute this set whenever the classification of any cell changes from UNKNOWN to FREE or BLOCKED.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Target Selection Heuristic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall prioritize exploration frontier targets using a heuristic that:
(1) computes the estimated travel-time component using the same cell-to-cell traversal cost model defined in the path optimality criterion requirement, and
(2) adds a term that prefers frontiers expected to increase the number of newly observable cells,
and shall select targets that minimize this combined heuristic while ensuring that the estimated time to reach and explore the target does not exceed the remaining exploration time defined by the time-aware planning requirement.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.2 Wall Detection -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Front Wall Detection From Ultrasonic</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret a front ultrasonic distance measurement d as a front wall in the current maze cell if the closed interval [d-12 cm, d+12 cm], derived from the ultrasonic uncertainty model, intersects the expected robot-center-to-wall distance interval for the current cell and pose that is computed from the 17.2 cm cell size and the 11 cm robot diameter.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Side Wall Detection From IR</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall interpret an active obstacle indication from a left or right infrared sensor as a wall located along the corresponding side of the current maze cell if the robot’s pose is aligned to the maze axes within a configurable angular tolerance not exceeding 10 degrees.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Proximity Thresholding</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall apply configurable numeric thresholds and hysteresis to filtered ultrasonic distance measurements to distinguish between free space and wall presence, such that single-sample noise or transient spikes do not cause flip-flopping between wall and free classifications.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Avoidance Maneuvers</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall command motor speeds to execute avoidance maneuvers (such as stopping and turning, or arc turns) when front or side wall detections indicate that the predicted robot trajectory would intersect a wall within one cell length, and shall select maneuvers that respect the robot footprint and minimum clearance margin so that collisions are prevented while maintaining progress toward exploration or path-planning goals.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.3 Create Map -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Data Structure</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an in-memory grid map data structure representing the 4x8 maze, where each cell and each inter-cell wall segment is explicitly stored with its classification and can be addressed by integer coordinates (row, column) aligned with the assumed physical maze geometry.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell and Wall Update From Sensors</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall update the grid map cells and wall segments based on processed ultrasonic and infrared measurements obtained while the pose-estimation module indicates that the robot is located at a cell center or during a transition between adjacent cell centers, marking corresponding walls as PRESENT or ABSENT and updating adjacent cells as FREE if traversed without collision.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Unknown Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initialize all cells and wall segments in the 4x8 grid map to an UNKNOWN classification at system startup prior to any sensor-based observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Start Cell Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall designate a fixed coordinate in the grid map as the start cell at initialization, set its classification to FREE, and maintain a record of this coordinate for use in return-to-start and second-run behaviors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Static Map Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.4.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall treat once-observed wall and free classifications in the grid map as immutable for the duration of a mission, such that:
(1) cell states may change only from UNKNOWN to FREE or UNKNOWN to BLOCKED and shall not revert to UNKNOWN within a mission, and
(2) wall segment states may change only from UNKNOWN to PRESENT or UNKNOWN to ABSENT and shall not change between PRESENT and ABSENT or revert to UNKNOWN within a mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.6">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Map Completeness Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define the map as complete when no cell and no inter-cell wall segment in the grid map remains in the UNKNOWN state, and shall provide a boolean indication of this condition to the mission control state machine.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.3.7">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Map Access Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a grid map access interface that offers:
(1) functions to query the classification of any cell and wall segment by (row, column) indices,
(2) functions to update the classification of cells and wall segments, and
(3) an event mechanism or callback registration by which other modules can be notified when specific cells or walls change classification,
and shall ensure that all map queries, updates, and classification-change notifications occur within the context of the periodic control loop execution so that map access is single-threaded and does not require additional synchronization.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.4 Cell Classification -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Classification Enumeration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall represent each maze cell’s state using an enumeration with at least the values {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}, shall ensure that each cell in the grid map is always in exactly one of these states, and shall allow cell state transitions only from UNKNOWN to FREE or from UNKNOWN to BLOCKED during a mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Segment Classification Enumeration</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.5</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall represent each wall segment between adjacent cells using an enumeration with at least the values {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}, and shall allow wall segment state transitions only from UNKNOWN to PRESENT or from UNKNOWN to ABSENT during a mission, so that once a wall is classified as PRESENT or ABSENT it shall not change state or revert to UNKNOWN in that mission.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Free Cell Confirmation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall mark a cell as FREE when the robot has successfully traversed into the cell without detecting a collision or blocking wall on the entry face, and no contradictory evidence, as defined by the sensor consistency-check requirement, has been accumulated for that cell.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.4.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Blocked Cell Inference</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall mark a neighboring cell as BLOCKED if a wall segment between the current cell and that neighbor is classified as PRESENT, and shall never issue movement commands that attempt to enter a cell classified as BLOCKED.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--MAP--1.5 Time Constraint -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Global Mapping Time Limit</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enforce a global time limit of 5 minutes from the start of exploration, after which it shall cease further exploration moves and signal to the mission control state machine that a timeout condition has occurred to initiate RETURN_TO_START, regardless of mapping completeness.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Time-Aware Planning</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.3</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall estimate remaining exploration time based on elapsed time and a configurable parameter representing the nominal time to traverse one cell at exploration speed, and shall avoid selecting exploration targets that cannot be reasonably reached and mapped before the 5 minute exploration time limit.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--MAP--1.5.3">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Nominal Cell Traversal Duration Parameter</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain a configurable parameter representing the nominal time required to traverse one maze cell at exploration speed, expressed in milliseconds, and shall make this parameter available to time-aware planning and exploration modules for remaining-time estimation.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--PLAN--1.1 Path Planning -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Based Path Planner</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a cell-based path planning algorithm (such as Dijkstra or A*) operating on the 4x8 grid map, where nodes correspond to FREE cells and edges connect orthogonally adjacent FREE cells (4-connected grid) that are not separated by PRESENT walls.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Path Optimality Criterion</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define path optimality as minimizing total traversal cost, where each move between orthogonally adjacent FREE cells has a non-negative cost that may be parameterized to distinguish straight-travel and turning penalties, and shall compute paths that minimize the sum of such costs between a given start and goal region.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--ENV--3.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall treat the selected 2x2 goal region as a set of up to four FREE goal cells and shall compute an optimal path from a given start cell to any of these goal cells, selecting the path with minimal traversal cost.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Replanning Capability</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.7</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall recompute planned paths whenever newly acquired map information marks previously assumed FREE cells or ABSENT walls as BLOCKED or PRESENT and the current path would otherwise traverse those blocked cells or walls, using the grid map access interface to detect invalidation events.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--PLAN--1.1.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Planning Failure Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect and signal a planning failure when no path exists between the current cell and the desired target or goal region in the current map, so that higher-level logic can report failure or select alternative behavior.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RUN--1.1 Return to Start -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--EVENT--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a return-to-start service that, when invoked by the mission control state machine after receipt of either an EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event or an EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event, computes a path from the robot’s current cell to the designated start cell using the path planning algorithm and current grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Return Path Execution</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall execute the computed return path cell by cell by issuing motor speed commands that move the robot between cell centers using motion primitives, while monitoring sensors to avoid collisions and triggering replanning if the path becomes invalid due to updated map information.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RUN--1.2 Second Run and HL--RUN--1.3 Efficient Path Execution -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Initialization</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RUN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall initiate the SECOND_RUN state in the mission control state machine after the robot has returned to the start cell and exploration has been declared complete by the exploration module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fastest Path Computation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--ENV--3.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall compute the fastest path from the start cell to the selected goal region using the grid map and path planner by configuring the traversal cost model parameters so that the resulting path minimizes an estimate of physical travel time during the second run.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Fast Path Motion Profile</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall execute the fastest path using motor speed commands that increase translational speed relative to exploration while limiting the commanded speeds to computed maximum permissible values that ensure the robot can safely stop before a wall given the configured sensor sampling rate, emergency-stop threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.4">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Success Criteria</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall declare the second run a success when the robot reaches any FREE cell in the 2x2 goal region following the fastest path without any detected collision; otherwise it shall declare the second run a failure.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RUN--1.2.5">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Second Run Status Reporting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide a boolean or enumerated status output indicating success or failure of the second run upon completion or abort of the SECOND_RUN state for use by the mission control state machine and external reporting.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RELIAB--1.1 Collision Avoidance -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.1.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Minimum Wall Clearance</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall enforce a configurable minimum clearance margin M &gt; 0 cm between the robot’s circular footprint of radius 5.5 cm and any wall position derived from the grid map, where M shall be selected to cover estimated worst-case pose and wall localization errors based on the ultrasonic uncertainty model, and shall ensure that planned and executed trajectories do not violate this clearance when following ideal commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.1.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Emergency Stop on Imminent Collision</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall immediately command both motors to speed 0 by invoking the motor command interface if filtered sensor data indicates an obstacle or wall within a configurable emergency distance threshold shorter than the nominal stopping distance at the current speed, and shall not resume movement until a new safe trajectory has been established.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--RELIAB--1.2 Sensor Noise Handling -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.2.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Sampling and Filtering</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall sample ultrasonic and infrared sensors at a configurable rate in the range [10, 50] Hz, with a default value of 20 Hz and timing jitter not exceeding a specified tolerance, and shall apply temporal filtering (such as moving average or median filters) to the sampled data to reduce the effect of random noise before using the data for wall detection or planning decisions, and shall perform this sampling once per iteration of the periodic control loop.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--RELIAB--1.2.2">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Consistency Checks on Sensor Data</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall compare new sensor-based wall observations against existing map entries and shall treat large, isolated discrepancies as potential sensor errors, requiring at least N configurable consecutive sensor readings that indicate a wall where the map currently stores FREE or ABSENT before changing the established wall or cell classification, where N shall be an integer greater than or equal to 2 with a documented default value of 3 and a recommended configuration range 2 ≤ N ≤ 10.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--1.1 Sensor Processing -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Sensor Abstraction Layer</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a sensor abstraction layer that wraps the ultrasonic_get_distance and infrared_get_dsl_status/infrared_get_dsr_status functions and exposes normalized sensor data structures to higher-level modules, including for each control cycle:
(1) an ultrasonic measurement represented as (distance_cm, timestamp), where distance_cm is a float in centimeters in the robot-forward frame, and
(2) infrared measurements represented as (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp), where each flag is a binary obstacle indication and timestamp is the acquisition time.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Invalid Sensor Reading Handling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect invalid or out-of-range sensor return values, such as negative distances or implementation-specific saturation codes, and shall ignore these readings or replace them with safe default estimates rather than using them directly for mapping or control decisions.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--1.2 Actuator Control -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Motor Command Interface</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall control the differential drive motors exclusively via the function motor_set(uint8_t left_speed, uint8_t right_speed), using integer speed values in the range [0,100] for each motor, and shall invoke motor_set at most once per iteration of the periodic control loop at the control loop frequency.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--1.2.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Speed Command Rate Limiting</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall limit the rate of change of successive motor_set speed commands by enforcing configurable maximum increments per control cycle for left and right speeds to avoid abrupt accelerations or decelerations that could cause wheel slippage or loss of control.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--2.1, 2.2, 2.3 Ultrasonic -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Distance Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, once per sensor sampling period defined by the noise-handling requirement and synchronized with the periodic control loop, call ultrasonic_get_distance() and interpret the returned float value as the distance in centimeters to the nearest front obstacle along the sensor beam in the robot-forward frame.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Ultrasonic Uncertainty Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall model each ultrasonic distance measurement as having an uncertainty interval of at least ±12 cm around the measured distance value and shall incorporate this interval into wall distance estimation, collision risk computations, and clearance-margin evaluations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--INTERF--3.x IR sensors -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Status Acquisition</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, at each sensor sampling period synchronized with the periodic control loop, call infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status() and interpret each returned uint8_t value as a binary obstacle detection flag for the respective left and right infrared sensors.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Effective Range Assumption</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall assume that a positive obstacle indication from an infrared sensor corresponds to an obstacle located approximately 4 cm from the sensor along its measurement direction and shall use this nominal distance when inferring side wall positions in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INTERF--3.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>IR Orientation Compensation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--3.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall account for the approximately 25 degree mounting angle of each infrared sensor relative to the robot front direction when transforming infrared obstacle detections into equivalent lateral wall distances and positions in the maze reference frame.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--1.1 Robot Shape -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Robot Footprint Model</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall model the robot as a circle of radius 5.5 cm when checking for possible collisions with walls located at cell boundaries spaced approximately 17.2 cm apart and when evaluating clearance against the minimum clearance margin.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--2.1 Differential Drive -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Differential Drive Kinematics</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--1.2.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement kinematic equations for a differential drive robot to estimate changes in robot orientation and position over time based on the left and right motor speed commands and the control-loop period T or measured cycle duration from the scheduling module, without assuming constant rotational speed.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Center Motion Primitives</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall provide motion primitives that move the robot from one maze cell center to an adjacent cell center and turn in place to discrete headings aligned with maze axes, using sequences of motor_set commands whose durations and speeds are derived from the differential-drive kinematics and cell dimension of approximately 17.2 cm.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--HARDWARE--2.3 Translational Velocity -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1">
    <Type>NFR</Type>
    <Name>Speed Limitation for Safety</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--RELIAB--1.1.2</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--INTERF--2.3.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall constrain the commanded motor speeds such that the resulting translational speed does not exceed a configured maximum below the 200 cm/s hardware capability, where this maximum speed is computed to ensure that, given the configured sensor sampling rate, emergency-stop distance threshold, and ultrasonic uncertainty, the robot can safely stop before reaching a detected wall.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- LLRs refining HL--ENV--1.x Maze properties -->
  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Grid Coordinate System</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall define a grid coordinate system with 4 rows and 8 columns for the maze, with a consistent convention for mapping physical positions to cell indices, such as defining row 0, column 0 as the start cell, and shall use this convention consistently across mapping, planning, and control modules.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.2.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Geometry Parameters</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall use the approximate cell dimension of 17.2 cm when transforming between estimated traveled distances and transitions between maze cell centers for pose estimation, motion primitive generation, and grid map updates.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.3.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Wall Geometry Parameters</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall use an approximate wall thickness of 1.6 cm when reasoning about the physical extent of walls relative to the robot footprint in collision and clearance checks.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--1.4.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Inter-Cell Wall Indexing</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--1.4</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall index possible wall positions as boundaries between horizontally and vertically adjacent cells and shall store wall presence or absence for each such boundary in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--3.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Identification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.4</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, upon completion of exploration, identify as candidate goal regions all contiguous 2x2 blocks of cells that are all classified as FREE and reachable from the start cell in the grid map.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--ENV--3.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Goal Region Selection</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--ENV--3.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--PLAN--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall, when multiple candidate 2x2 FREE regions exist, select as the maze goal region the one that minimizes the optimal path cost from the start cell according to the traversal cost metric defined for the path planner, and shall provide this selected region to the second-run planning module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <!-- Additional LLRs -->

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell-Level Pose Estimation</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--SCHED--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall maintain an estimate of the robot’s current maze cell index (row, column) and discrete heading aligned with the maze axes, updated in each control loop cycle by integrating the differential drive kinematics over the control-loop period T or measured cycle duration provided by the scheduling module and the issued motor speed commands.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.2">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Pose Correction Using Map Features</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--HARDWARE--2.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.2.1</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.2.2</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall correct accumulated orientation and position error in the pose estimate when the robot is aligned with maze axes and wall detections indicate proximity to known cell boundaries, by snapping the estimated heading to the nearest axis-aligned direction and adjusting the position to the nearest cell center consistent with the wall observations.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--POSE--1.1.3">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Cell Center Entry Notification</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.3</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--POSE--1.1.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall detect when the pose estimate crosses from one cell center to an adjacent cell center and shall notify the mapping module of the new current cell index so that cell and wall updates can be associated with the correct cell transition.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--EVENT--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Exploration Status Events</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.5</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RUN--1.1</Refines>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.3.6</DependsOn>
      <DependsOn>LL--MAP--1.5.1</DependsOn>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement an exploration-status module, integrated with the mission control state machine, that publishes EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events by enqueuing corresponding event records into a system event queue accessible to the mission control and return-to-start modules when, respectively, the map completeness criterion indicates a complete map or the global exploration time limit is reached.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--SCHED--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Periodic Control Loop Scheduling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--MAP--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--PLAN--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--RELIAB--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement a periodic control loop with a configurable period T such that the control loop frequency equals the sensor sampling rate defined in the sensor sampling requirement, and in each cycle it shall:
(1) acquire sensor readings via the sensor abstraction layer,
(2) update the grid map using the mapping module,
(3) update the mission control state machine,
(4) compute or update the current path as required by the active state, and
(5) issue motor_set commands via the motion control module.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>

  <Requirement ID="LL--INIT--1.1.1">
    <Type>FR</Type>
    <Name>Initialization Completion Signaling</Name>
    <Relationships>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.1</Refines>
      <Refines>HL--INTERF--1.2</Refines>
    </Relationships>
    <Content>
The software shall implement an initialization module that, after all required hardware and software initialization routines have successfully completed, sets an INIT_COMPLETED flag or publishes an INIT_COMPLETED event within the main execution context, and the mission control state machine shall only transition from IDLE to EXPLORE after this indication is present.
    </Content>
  </Requirement>
</Requirements>
<Design>
    <Components version="1">
        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--1</ID>
            <Name>Mission Control State Machine</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Orchestrates the high-level behaviour of the robot for maze exploration, return to start, and second run.
                Owns the top-level mission state machine with states {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                Within the periodic control loop it:
                - Reads initialization completion, exploration status, exploration timeout, sensor availability and second-run status.
                - Requests frontier targets from the Frontier Generation module and selects exploration targets using the Exploration Target Selector.
                - Requests paths from the Cell-based Path Planner for exploration frontiers, return-to-start, and second-run.
                - Commands the Motion Controller to execute motion primitives that follow the current path.
                - Invokes Return-to-start Service and Second-run Planning services as required by the current mission state.
                - Maintains and publishes final second-run status in COMPLETED state.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request message sent from Mission Control to Frontier Generation module to compute or refresh the current set of frontier cells.
                                Contains:
                                - requester_id: enum = MISSION_CONTROL
                                - current_cell: (row, col) integer indices
                                - request_type: {FULL_RECOMPUTE, USE_CACHED_IF_VALID}
                                Timing: issued during EXPLORE state when a new target is needed or existing target/path invalidated.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_FrontierSubscription</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Registration request for classification-change notifications relevant to frontiers.
                                Fields:
                                - callback_id to be invoked when UNKNOWN-&gt;{FREE,BLOCKED} transitions occur.
                                Used to trigger target recomputation if relevant cells change.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_FrontierSet</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Response from Frontier Generation containing the current frontier set.
                                Data:
                                - frontier_cells: array of frontier entries:
                                  each frontier entry:
                                     cell_row: uint8_t
                                     cell_col: uint8_t
                                     is_valid: bool
                                - generation_timestamp: uint32
                                Frontier cells are defined as UNKNOWN cells with at least one 4-neighbour FREE cell.
                                If no frontier exists, array length == 0.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_Notification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Asynchronous notification that at least one cell transitioned from UNKNOWN to FREE/BLOCKED.
                                Data:
                                - changed_cells: list of (row, col) indices
                                Used by Mission Control to decide to discard current frontier target and re-run selection.
                                Delivered in EXPLORE state only.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request from Mission Control to Cell-based Path Planner.
                                Fields:
                                - request_id: unique integer
                                - path_type: {EXPLORATION_TO_FRONTIER, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN_TO_GOAL}
                                - start_cell: (row, col)
                                - goal_cells: array of goal cell coordinates (row, col); for frontier exploration a single goal, for goal region multiple candidates.
                                - traversal_cost_profile: identifier selecting cost parameter set
                                  e.g. {EXPLORATION_PROFILE, FASTEST_TIME_PROFILE}
                                The planner computes an optimal path (Dijkstra or A*) restricted to FREE cells and edges not crossing PRESENT walls.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_PathResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Response from Cell-based Path Planner to Mission Control.
                                Fields:
                                - request_id: echoes MC_PathRequest.request_id
                                - status: {SUCCESS, FAILURE_NO_PATH}
                                - path_cells: ordered list of (row, col) from start to chosen goal cell; valid if status == SUCCESS
                                - total_cost: float, sum of edge traversal costs
                                If status == FAILURE_NO_PATH, Mission Control triggers replanning or planning-failure handling depending on current mission state.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                High-level motion command to Motion Controller to execute or stop path-following.
                                Fields:
                                - command_type: {EXECUTE_PATH, STOP, EMERGENCY_STOP_ACK}
                                - path_descriptor:
                                   - cell_sequence: list of (row, col) grid cells to traverse
                                   - speed_profile: {EXPLORATION, RETURN, SECOND_RUN_FAST}
                                - start_index: index into cell_sequence from which to start or resume
                                When command_type == EXECUTE_PATH, Motion Controller converts this into motion primitives between cell centers.
                                When STOP, Motion Controller ceases issuing motion and holds current pose.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MissionSpeedProfileUpdate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional update to speed profile parameters (e.g. during transition from EXPLORE/RETURN to SECOND_RUN).
                                Contains:
                                - profile_type: {EXPLORATION, SECOND_RUN_FAST}
                                - max_trans_speed_cm_s
                                - accel_limits
                                Motion Controller applies these values when generating primitives and mapping to motor_set speeds.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathExecutionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status feedback from Motion Controller.
                                Fields:
                                - execution_state: {IDLE, EXECUTING, BLOCKED, COMPLETED, EMERGENCY_STOP}
                                - current_cell: (row, col) according to pose estimation
                                - next_waypoint_index: index of next target cell in path
                                - collision_risk_flag: bool, true if emergency-stop triggered
                                Mission Control uses this to detect completion of exploration or return paths, and to trigger replanning on BLOCKED or EMERGENCY_STOP.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--5</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationStartNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification to Exploration-Status/Timer module that EXPLORE state has started.
                                Fields:
                                - exploration_start_timestamp: uint32 milliseconds since boot
                                Used for enforcing global 5 minute limit.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationStopNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notification that EXPLORE state has terminated and RETURN_TO_START is being initiated.
                                Used so the timer module can stop timing and avoid duplicate timeout events.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_ExplorationCompletedEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event dequeued from system event queue indicating map completeness.
                                Contains:
                                - event_type: EXPLORATION_COMPLETED
                                - timestamp_ms
                                When received while in EXPLORE, triggers a transition to RETURN_TO_START.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_ExplorationTimeoutEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event dequeued from system event queue indicating expiration of 5 minute exploration limit.
                                Contains:
                                - event_type: EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT
                                - timestamp_ms
                                When received while in EXPLORE, triggers a transition to RETURN_TO_START regardless of map completeness.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_InitStatusQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional polling query or shared flag read for INIT_COMPLETED.
                                Implemented as direct read of a boolean field in initialization module.
                                Used in IDLE state to determine when to transition to EXPLORE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_COMPLETED</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Flag/event published by Initialization module once all startup routines are complete.
                                Mission Control checks this flag in each control loop iteration while in IDLE.
                                On first observation INIT_COMPLETED == true and at least one valid sensor set, transitions to EXPLORE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SensorAvailabilityQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Read access to latest normalized sensor data (ultrasonic, IR) via Sensor Abstraction Layer.
                                Mission Control queries whether at least one valid set of measurements is available to satisfy exploration start condition.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_SensorSnapshot</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Structure populated each control cycle by the Sensor Abstraction Layer:
                                - ultrasonic: (distance_cm, timestamp, valid_flag)
                                - infrared: (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp, valid_flag)
                                Mission Control examines valid_flag(s) to determine that at least one valid sensor set is available before entering EXPLORE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ReturnToStartInvoke</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Logical invocation of Return-to-start Service.
                                Triggered when entering RETURN_TO_START state.
                                Fields:
                                - trigger_source: {EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT}
                                - current_cell: (row, col) from pose estimation
                                - start_cell: (row, col) from grid map
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SecondRunInvoke</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Invocation of Second-run Planning Service.
                                Occurs after RETURN_TO_START completes and exploration has been declared complete.
                                Fields:
                                - start_cell: (row, col)
                                - goal_region_descriptor: 2x2 block (row0,col0) representing goal candidate provided by goal-region module
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_ReturnPathStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status structure from Return-to-start Service.
                                Fields:
                                - status: {PATH_COMPUTED, PATH_PLANNING_FAILED}
                                - path_cells: list of (row, col) if PATH_COMPUTED
                                Mission Control forwards path to Motion Controller and monitors execution.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_SecondRunPlanStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Status structure from Second-run Planning Service.
                                Fields:
                                - status: {FASTEST_PATH_COMPUTED, GOAL_UNREACHABLE}
                                - fastest_path_cells: list of (row, col) if FASTEST_PATH_COMPUTED
                                Mission Control uses this to decide whether SECOND_RUN can execute and to update final status.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_SecondRunExecutionResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Final result of executing the fastest path during SECOND_RUN.
                                Fields:
                                - result: {SECOND_RUN_SUCCESS, SECOND_RUN_FAILURE}
                                - reached_goal_cell: optional (row, col) if success
                                - failure_reason: optional enum {COLLISION_DETECTED, PATH_BLOCKED, PLANNING_FAILURE}
                                Mission Control stores this result and remains in COMPLETED state for external reporting.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_GoalRegionQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request to Goal Region Identification/Selection module after exploration is complete.
                                Fields:
                                - start_cell: (row, col)
                                Module returns selected 2x2 goal region minimizing path cost.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_SelectedGoalRegion</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Response with selected 2x2 FREE, reachable goal region.
                                Fields:
                                - region_cells: up to four (row, col) cells representing the region
                                - representative_corner: (row, col) minimal indices describing region base
                                Mission Control passes these goal cells to Second-run Planning Service.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                Executed once per iteration of the periodic control loop (CMP--18) after sensor and grid map updates.
                Logic:
                - Read current mission state (IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED).
                - In IDLE:
                  * Read INIT_COMPLETED flag from Initialization module (CMP--19).
                  * Read latest SAL_SensorSnapshot from Sensor Abstraction Layer (CMP--11).
                  * If INIT_COMPLETED == true AND at least one valid set of ultrasonic/IR measurements is present, transition to EXPLORE, notify Exploration-Status (MC_ExplorationStartNotification), and clear any previous mission data.
                - In EXPLORE:
                  * If an EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event is available from Exploration-Status module, trigger transition to RETURN_TO_START with trigger_source = COMPLETED.
                  * Else if an EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event is available, trigger transition to RETURN_TO_START with trigger_source = TIMEOUT.
                  * Else:
                    - If no active exploration path or current path execution is COMPLETED or BLOCKED, request frontier set from Frontier Generation (MC_ExplorationRequest).
                    - Apply Exploration Target Selection heuristic (internally or via CMP--2/3) to choose next frontier target.
                    - Send MC_PathRequest to Cell-based Path Planner for EXPLORATION_TO_FRONTIER path. On SUCCESS, send MC_MotionCommand EXECUTE_PATH with EXPLORATION speed profile to Motion Controller.
                    - Listen for FG_Notification (classification changes) or MC_PathExecutionStatus == BLOCKED/EMERGENCY_STOP to trigger replanning: issue MC_PathRequest again to recompute path to current or new target.
                - In RETURN_TO_START:
                  * On entry, send MC_ReturnToStartInvoke to Return-to-start Service, which uses planner and grid map.
                  * On RS_ReturnPathStatus == PATH_COMPUTED, send MC_MotionCommand EXECUTE_PATH with RETURN speed profile to Motion Controller.
                  * Monitor MC_PathExecutionStatus; when EXECUTION COMPLETED and current_cell == start_cell, declare return path complete and trigger transition to SECOND_RUN if exploration complete, otherwise directly to COMPLETED (failure).
                  * On PATH_PLANNING_FAILED or if Motion Controller reports persistent BLOCKED with no alternative path, abort return, set mission final status to failure, transition to COMPLETED.
                - In SECOND_RUN:
                  * On entry, verify exploration is complete and robot is at start_cell using pose estimate (CMP--17) and map completeness (CMP--10).
                  * Issue MC_GoalRegionQuery to Goal Region module; receive GR_SelectedGoalRegion.
                  * Issue MC_SecondRunInvoke to Second-run Planning Service; on FASTEST_PATH_COMPUTED, update MissionSpeedProfileUpdate to SECOND_RUN_FAST and send MC_MotionCommand EXECUTE_PATH with SECOND_RUN_FAST profile.
                  * Monitor MC_PathExecutionStatus; on EXECUTION COMPLETED and reached goal region (SR_SecondRunExecutionResult == SECOND_RUN_SUCCESS), store success status; on failure or collision, store failure status; then transition to COMPLETED.
                - In COMPLETED:
                  * Cease issuing MC_MotionCommand EXECUTE_PATH; optionally send STOP to Motion Controller once.
                  * Maintain last second-run status; respond to external status queries.
                  * Remain in COMPLETED until system reset.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Mission Control executes once per iteration of the periodic control loop with period T (CMP--18, LL--SCHED--1.1.1). T is equal to the sensor sampling period (LL--RELIAB--1.2.1).
                - State evaluation and transitions are deterministic: in each cycle, only one sequence of guards and transitions is valid for a given set of inputs.
                - Exploration behaviour:
                  * Frontier requests and path requests are made opportunistically when no active valid path exists; not more than one MC_PathRequest per cycle.
                  * Exploration timeout enforced by Exploration-Status module: global time limit of 5 minutes (LL--MAP--1.5.1) from EXPLORE start timestamp. Mission Control reacts within one control cycle after timeout event is generated.
                - Return-to-start and SECOND_RUN path computations are triggered once per respective state entry; replanning is limited to cases where map updates invalidate current path (LL--PLAN--1.1.4).
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Mission control state is always exactly one of {IDLE, EXPLORE, RETURN_TO_START, SECOND_RUN, COMPLETED}.
                - Mission Control does not issue motion commands (MC_MotionCommand EXECUTE_PATH) while in IDLE or COMPLETED.
                - Transitions are deterministic: for any input combination, at most one outgoing transition from a given state is taken per cycle.
                - A SECOND_RUN state can only be entered after a RETURN_TO_START state has completed and exploration has been declared complete (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event received).
                - Once COMPLETED is entered, no further transitions to other states occur without system reset.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Planning Failure in RETURN_TO_START:
                  * Condition: RS_ReturnPathStatus.status == PATH_PLANNING_FAILED or planner indicates no path to start cell (LL--PLAN--1.1.5).
                  * Effect: Mission Control sets mission result to failure, transitions to COMPLETED, issues STOP command to Motion Controller.
                - Planning Failure in SECOND_RUN:
                  * Condition: SR_SecondRunPlanStatus.status == GOAL_UNREACHABLE or planner reports failure to compute fastest path to selected goal region.
                  * Effect: Mission Control sets second-run status to failure, transitions to COMPLETED.
                - Motion Execution Blocked:
                  * Condition: MC_PathExecutionStatus.execution_state == BLOCKED or EMERGENCY_STOP for more than a configured number of cycles and no alternative path can be found.
                  * Effect: In EXPLORE, triggers target reselection and replanning; if no reachable frontier remains, triggers EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event via Exploration-Status or transitions to RETURN_TO_START depending on implementation.
                  * In RETURN_TO_START, leads to replanning; if still no path, treated as planning failure as above.
                  * In SECOND_RUN, leads to second-run failure and transition to COMPLETED.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1; LL--MAP--1.1.2; LL--MAP--1.1.3; LL--MAP--1.1.4; LL--MAP--1.1.5; LL--MAP--1.1.6;
                LL--MAP--1.3.6; LL--MAP--1.5.1; LL--MAP--1.5.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.1; LL--PLAN--1.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.3;
                LL--PLAN--1.1.4; LL--PLAN--1.1.5; LL--RUN--1.1.1; LL--RUN--1.1.2; LL--RUN--1.2.1; LL--RUN--1.2.2;
                LL--RUN--1.2.3; LL--RUN--1.2.4; LL--RUN--1.2.5; LL--RELIAB--1.1.2; LL--RELIAB--1.2.1; LL--INTERF--1.1.1;
                LL--INTERF--1.2.1; LL--SCHED--1.1.1; LL--EVENT--1.1.1; LL--INIT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--2</ID>
            <Name>Frontier Generation and Exploration Target Selection</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintains and computes the set of frontier cells and selects exploration targets using a heuristic considering travel time and expected information gain, subject to remaining exploration time constraints.
                Responsibilities:
                - Traverse the grid map (CMP--10) to compute frontier set F = {cells that are UNKNOWN and are 4-neighbours of at least one FREE cell}.
                - Recompute frontier set when any cell changes classification from UNKNOWN to FREE/BLOCKED.
                - Evaluate each frontier cell using combined heuristic:
                  * h_total = travel_time_estimate + information_gain_term, using same cost model as path planner (LL--PLAN--1.1.2) and estimation of newly observable cells.
                - Filter out candidate targets whose estimated time to reach and explore exceeds remaining exploration time (LL--MAP--1.5.2, LL--MAP--1.5.3).
                - Provide selected target cell to Mission Control and Path Planner.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_MapQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to Grid Map module to iterate over cells and query cell classification and neighbour relationships.
                                The Frontier Generation module uses:
                                - get_cell_state(row, col) -&gt; {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}
                                - get_neighbours(row, col) -&gt; list of 4-connected neighbour coordinates
                                - get_wall_between(cell_a, cell_b) to ensure adjacency validity if needed.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_ClassificationChangeNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Asynchronous notifications when any cell changes from UNKNOWN to FREE or UNKNOWN to BLOCKED.
                                Used to trigger recomputation:
                                - For each changed cell, Frontier Generation checks if it or its neighbours become/stop being frontiers.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_FrontierSet</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Set of frontier cells returned in response to MC_ExplorationRequest.
                                See definition in CMP--1.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_Notification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1 description. Emitted when frontier set potentially changed after map updates.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1 description. Triggers (re)computation of frontier set and, optionally, selection of new target.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_TravelTimeEstimateRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                For each frontier candidate, Frontier Generation can ask the path planner to estimate travel cost from current cell to that candidate using the cell-based cost model.
                                Fields:
                                - start_cell: (row, col)
                                - target_cells: list of frontier cells to evaluate
                                - cost_profile: EXPLORATION_PROFILE
                                Planner may respond with approximate costs without full path enumeration if optimization is required.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_TravelTimeEstimateResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provides estimated travel costs (or INFEASIBLE) for each target cell.
                                Used in heuristic computation h_total.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--5</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_RemainingTimeQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                The module queries Exploration-Status/Timer for current remaining exploration time:
                                - elapsed_ms since exploration start
                                - remaining_ms before 5 minute limit.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_RemainingTimeInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Response with remaining exploration time and nominal per-cell traversal duration parameter.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Frontier Generation:
                  * Executed on-demand when Mission Control issues MC_ExplorationRequest or when GM_ClassificationChangeNotification is received.
                  * Implementation:
                    - Iterate over all grid cells (4x8) or maintain incremental frontier list.
                    - For each cell (r,c):
                        if get_cell_state(r,c) == UNKNOWN:
                            for each 4-neighbour n in get_neighbours(r,c):
                                if get_cell_state(n) == FREE:
                                    mark (r,c) as frontier, break.
                    - Store frontier set in an internal data structure (array of cell indices and meta-data).
                  * Map-completeness check is not directly a responsibility here but frontier emptiness plus map completeness can be used to optimise exploration completion logic.
                - Target Selection:
                  * Triggered after frontier set computation when Mission Control needs a new target.
                  * For each frontier cell f:
                     - Request or compute travel_time_estimate(f) using path planning cost model and/or nominal cell traversal duration:
                       travel_time_estimate_ms ≈ path_cost(f) * cell_traversal_time_ms (for unit cost edges) or from planner-provided total_cost mapped to time.
                     - Information gain estimate:
                        * Estimate number of UNKNOWN cells that would become observable from f, e.g. count of UNKNOWN neighbours plus extrapolated visibility along free corridors.
                        * Define info_gain_term = -k * expected_new_cells, where k &gt; 0 is configurable, so more expected new cells reduces heuristic.
                     - Combined heuristic:
                        h_total(f) = alpha * travel_time_estimate_ms + beta * info_gain_term.
                        alpha, beta configurable weighting parameters.
                     - Remaining time feasibility check:
                        * Use ES_RemainingTimeInfo.remaining_ms and ensure:
                          travel_time_estimate_ms + exploration_buffer_ms &lt;= remaining_ms
                          where exploration_buffer_ms accounts for time to perform local sensing at target cell.
                        * Frontier cells failing this check are discarded.
                  * Select f* = argmin_f h_total(f) among feasible frontiers.
                  * Return selected target to Mission Control via FG_FrontierSet (single-element selection or by having Mission Control choose based on extended metadata).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Frontier recomputation is executed within the periodic control loop after map update and before mission control state machine execution when triggered.
                - For the small 4x8 grid, full recomputation can be performed in a single cycle without timing issues.
                - Travel time estimates using planner interface must not block control loop for more than one cycle; an implementation may:
                  * use cached approximate distances (e.g. Manhattan distance weighted by nominal cell traversal time), or
                  * limit number of evaluated frontiers per cycle and spread computation over multiple cycles.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Frontier cells are always a subset of UNKNOWN cells.
                - Every frontier cell has at least one 4-neighbour FREE cell.
                - Frontier set is recomputed whenever any cell changes from UNKNOWN to FREE/BLOCKED; cached frontier entries referencing non-UNKNOWN cells are purged.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No Feasible Frontier:
                  * Condition: after heuristic filtering using remaining time, no frontier remains feasible.
                  * Effect: Module returns empty frontier set; Mission Control may treat this as exploration completion or request immediate RETURN_TO_START.
                - Path Infeasible to Frontier:
                  * Condition: travel_time_estimate(f) is infinite/INFEASIBLE due to planner failure (blocked paths).
                  * Effect: Frontier cell f is discarded from candidate set; if all are infeasible, same as "No Feasible Frontier".
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.4; LL--MAP--1.1.5; LL--MAP--1.1.6; LL--MAP--1.1.6;
                LL--MAP--1.1.6; LL--MAP--1.1.6;
                LL--MAP--1.1.6; LL--MAP--1.1.6;
                LL--MAP--1.1.6; LL--MAP--1.1.6;
                LL--MAP--1.1.6; LL--MAP--1.3.1; LL--MAP--1.3.7; LL--MAP--1.5.2; LL--MAP--1.5.3;
                LL--PLAN--1.1.1; LL--PLAN--1.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--3</ID>
            <Name>Cell-Based Path Planner</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provides grid-based path planning capabilities for exploration, return-to-start, and second run, operating on the 4x8 grid map.
                Responsibilities:
                - Implement Dijkstra or A* over the grid where nodes are FREE cells and edges connect 4-neighbour FREE cells with no PRESENT wall between them.
                - Use a customizable traversal cost model distinguishing straight travel and turning penalties and able to represent time-based constraints.
                - Support goal-region handling: accept multiple goal cells and find minimum-cost path.
                - Detect and report planning failures when no path exists.
                - Support replanning when map updates invalidate part of the current path.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_MapQueries</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Grid map queries used by planner:
                                - get_cell_state(row, col)
                                - get_wall_between(cell_a, cell_b) -&gt; wall state {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}
                                - get_start_cell(), get_goal_region()
                                All queries must be executed during the control loop and are single-threaded.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_PathInvalidationEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Event from Grid Map Signalling that one or more cells/walls that lie on the current active path were updated from UNKNOWN to BLOCKED or ABSENT to PRESENT.
                                Planner listens to this to trigger replanning (LL--PLAN--1.1.4).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_PathResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1 for format. Provided in reply to MC_PathRequest for all mission phases.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1 description. Triggers path computation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_TravelTimeEstimateResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--2; returns approximate path cost and/or time estimate for multiple frontier targets.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_TravelTimeEstimateRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--2; processed by computing path cost from start_cell to each target in target_cells using specified cost_profile, or returning INFEASIBLE if no path.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--12</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_FastestPathCostProfileUpdate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional configuration for traversal cost parameters used during second run.
                                Provided by Second Run Planning component.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_CostProfileConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Contains:
                                - straight_move_cost_weight
                                - turn_penalty_weight
                                - additional temporal scaling if needed.
                                Planner applies this to compute fastest-path w.r.t. estimated travel time.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Path computation:
                    * On reception of MC_PathRequest or FG_TravelTimeEstimateRequest, run A* or Dijkstra search.
                    * Node representation: (row, col, heading) or (row, col) with turn penalties evaluated on edges, depending on design.
                    * Successor generation:
                      - For each FREE 4-neighbour cell neighbour N of current cell C:
                         if wall_between(C, N) != PRESENT and N is FREE:
                             create edge from C to N.
                      - Cost:
                         base_move_cost = cost_straight if movement is straight relative to previous heading, else cost_turn (cost_turn &gt;= cost_straight).
                         Additional scaling to map cost units to estimated traversal time can be applied via traversal_cost_profile.
                    * Termination:
                      - For single-goal path (exploration and return-to-start): goal cell is provided by Mission Control.
                      - For goal region handling (LL--PLAN--1.1.3): treat all goal region cells as terminal nodes; algorithm stops when the first goal node is popped from priority queue (A*).
                    * Output:
                      - Reconstruct path by following predecessor links from goal node back to start.
                      - Return path (start..goal) and total_cost to requester.
                - Replanning:
                    * When GM_PathInvalidationEvent indicates path invalidation:
                       - Check if current active path segments cross updated cells/walls.
                       - If yes, recompute path from current cell (from Pose Estimation CMP--17) to target/goal using updated map.
                       - Notify Mission Control by sending PP_PathResponse with new path; Mission Control will update Motion Controller.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Path planning is triggered within the control loop; given the small grid (4x8), a full A*/Dijkstra run completes well within one cycle at sample rates [10,50] Hz.
                - Replanning is executed in the cycle immediately following a GM_PathInvalidationEvent or MC_PathRequest for replanning.
                - Travel-time estimate requests from Frontier Selection may be batched; planner may approximate cost by using simple grid metrics (e.g. Manhattan distance with turn penalties) when full search for each frontier is too costly.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Planner never uses BLOCKED cells as nodes and never creates edges across PRESENT walls.
                - All returned paths consist exclusively of FREE cells.
                - total_cost is non-negative and increases monotonically along the path.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Planning Failure:
                  * Condition: No path exists from start to any goal due to BLOCKED cells and PRESENT walls.
                  * Effect: status = FAILURE_NO_PATH in PP_PathResponse; caller (Mission Control, Return-to-start, Second Run) decides on alternative behaviour (e.g. mission failure).
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--PLAN--1.1.1; LL--PLAN--1.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.3; LL--PLAN--1.1.4; LL--PLAN--1.1.5;
                LL--MAP--1.3.1; LL--MAP--1.3.7; LL--MAP--1.4.1; LL--MAP--1.4.2; LL--ENV--3.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--4</ID>
            <Name>Motion Controller and Collision Avoidance</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Converts planned cell-based paths into motor_set commands that move the robot between cell centers while avoiding collisions and respecting kinematic constraints, minimum clearance margin, and speed limitations.
                Responsibilities:
                - Implement motion primitives to move from one cell center to adjacent cell centers and to turn in place (using differential drive kinematics).
                - Translate high-level path descriptions and speed profiles into sequences of motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) commands issued once per control loop.
                - Limit the rate of change of speed commands to avoid abrupt acceleration/deceleration.
                - Enforce speed limitations for safety, based on sensor sampling, emergency-stop distance, and ultrasonic uncertainty.
                - Monitor filtered sensor data to detect imminent collision and trigger emergency stops.
                - Execute wall avoidance maneuvers when obstacles are detected within one cell length of predicted trajectory.
                - Provide path execution status back to Mission Control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_CurrentPathFeedback</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional feedback to planner regarding which segment of the current path is active; not required for basic function but may be used to optimize replanning.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_PathResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provided indirectly via Mission Control (CMP--1) which issues MC_MotionCommand EXECUTE_PATH; Motion Controller reads cell_sequence and speed_profile.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathExecutionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1. Motion Controller populates this each control loop cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1. Commands Motion Controller to start/stop execution of a given path with specific speed profile.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MissionSpeedProfileUpdate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1. Updates internal speed limits used for each mission phase.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SensorUseRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Reads filtered sensor data used for collision detection and wall avoidance:
                                - front ultrasonic distance with uncertainty interval
                                - left/right IR obstacle flags and nominal distances.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Sensor Abstraction Layer:
                                - ultrasonic_filtered: float distance_cm, validity flag.
                                - infrared_filtered: left_flag, right_flag, optional debounced/hysteresis flags.
                                Motion Controller uses this for collision detection and maneuvers.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--13</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PoseQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Query current pose (cell index and heading) for mapping path waypoints to physical movement.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_CurrentEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Pose Estimation response:
                                - current_cell: (row, col)
                                - heading: discrete {NORTH, EAST, SOUTH, WEST}
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--14</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_KinematicParamsQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Query differential drive kinematics parameters:
                                - wheel_base (distance between drive wheels)
                                - wheel_radius scaling factor from motor_set speed to linear velocity.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>DD_KinematicParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provides constants used to map motor_set speeds to robot linear and angular velocities per sample period.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--16</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_EmergencyStopThresholdConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration for emergency-stop distance threshold and minimum clearance margin.
                                May be provided by Reliability/Safety module.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RE_SafetyLimits</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Contains:
                                - emergency_distance_cm
                                - min_clearance_margin_cm (M)
                                - max_safe_speed_cm_s
                                Motion Controller uses this to enforce speed and clearance constraints.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--15</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotorSet</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Calls LL motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) at most once per control cycle as required by LL--INTERF--1.2.1.
                                left_speed/right_speed in [0,100].
                                Motion Controller ensures rate-limiting constraints between successive invocations.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MotorInterfaceConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Contains motor characteristics or calibration constants (e.g. mapping from 0..100 to cm/s) used to derive traversal durations for primitives.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Each control loop cycle:
                  * If there is an active path and not in EMERGENCY_STOP:
                    - Determine current target cell from path cell_sequence and current waypoint index.
                    - Query pose estimate (POSE_CurrentEstimate) to know current cell and heading.
                    - If current cell == target cell:
                        advance waypoint index; if at end-of-path, set execution_state = COMPLETED and set both motor speeds to 0.
                    - Else:
                        compute motion primitive appropriate to move toward target cell:
                        - If heading not aligned towards target cell:
                           issue turn-in-place primitive: compute required rotation (±90°) and corresponding differential wheel speeds (left = -right, magnitude based on profile).
                        - Else:
                           issue forward-translation primitive: compute number of control cycles required to traverse 17.2 cm at current profile speed; maintain primitive progress state across cycles.
                  * Apply speed limitation:
                    - enforce |speed_new - speed_prev| ≤ max_increment_per_cycle for each wheel (LL--INTERF--1.2.2).
                    - clamp speeds to [0, max_safe_speed_profile], where max_safe_speed_profile ≤ max_safe_speed_cm_s from safety module and ≤ profile-specific max speed (exploration &lt; second-run).
                  * Collision avoidance:
                    - Read SAL_FilteredSensorData.
                    - Compute predicted stopping distance at current speed, using known deceleration capability and control loop period.
                    - Emergency stop:
                        if ultrasonic distance, considering ±12 cm uncertainty, is less than emergency_distance_threshold &lt; stopping_distance:
                            issue motor_set(0,0) immediately this cycle; set execution_state = EMERGENCY_STOP; notify Mission Control.
                            Remain stopped until Mission Control issues new safe trajectory.
                    - Wall avoidance maneuver:
                        if front or side wall detections indicate that predicted path will intersect a wall within one cell length:
                            design an avoidance primitive (e.g. stop, turn left or right ±90°, or arc turn) that respects robot footprint radius 5.5 cm, wall thickness 1.6 cm, and minimum clearance margin M, computed using geometric constraints from Additional Data (DAT--2, DAT--3).
                            execute avoidance primitive while preserving progress towards long-term goals (e.g. re-align with grid and continue exploration).
                  * If STOP command from Mission Control is active:
                     - issue motor_set(0,0), clear active path, set execution_state = IDLE.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - One motor_set invocation per control loop iteration (LL--INTERF--1.2.1) at frequency in [10,50] Hz defined by sensor sampling rate.
                - Motion primitives are parameterised in multiples of T, number_of_cycles = distance_to_travel / (speed_cm_per_s * T).
                - Emergency stop decisions are made every cycle, with latency bounded by one period T.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - motor_set is never called more than once in a single control loop cycle.
                - left_speed and right_speed values are always within [0,100].
                - Rate limit |Δspeed| per motor between consecutive cycles never exceeds configured maximums.
                - Active path is always a subset of FREE cells and respects PRESENT walls (enforced by planner).
                - If execution_state == EMERGENCY_STOP, commanded speeds remain 0 until new safe trajectory is established.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Emergency Stop:
                  * Trigger: imminent collision detected per LL--RELIAB--1.1.2.
                  * Effect: immediate motor_set(0,0); notify Mission Control via MC_PathExecutionStatus (EMERGENCY_STOP).
                - Wall Avoidance Failure:
                  * If avoidance primitives cannot find any manoeuvre that maintains required clearance margin M, Motion Controller triggers EMERGENCY_STOP and delegates decision to higher levels.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.4; LL--MAP--1.4.4; LL--RUN--1.1.2; LL--RUN--1.2.3;
                LL--INTERF--1.2.1; LL--INTERF--1.2.2;
                LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1; LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1; LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2; LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1;
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1; LL--RELIAB--1.1.2; LL--RELIAB--1.2.1; LL--MAP--1.5.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--5</ID>
            <Name>Exploration Status and Timer Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Monitors exploration progress and time to publish EXPLORATION_COMPLETED and EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT events, enforce global 5-minute limit, and provide remaining-time estimates to exploration modules.
                Responsibilities:
                - Record exploration start timestamp when mission control enters EXPLORE.
                - Track elapsed time in each control loop using scheduler timebase.
                - Query map completeness flag from Grid Map and publish EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event when map is complete.
                - Detect when elapsed exploration time reaches 5 minutes and publish EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event.
                - Insert events into system event queue accessible by Mission Control and Return-to-start service.
                - Provide remaining exploration time and nominal cell traversal parameter to Frontier-based exploration for time-aware planning.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_ExplorationCompletedEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1. Produced when map completeness criterion indicates completion.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_ExplorationTimeoutEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1. Produced when elapsed exploration time reaches or exceeds 5 minutes (300000 ms).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_RemainingTimeInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Response to FG_RemainingTimeQuery:
                                - elapsed_ms
                                - remaining_ms = max(0, 300000 - elapsed_ms)
                                - nominal_cell_traversal_ms (from Time-Aware Planning parameter).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationStartNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Indicates EXPLORE state entry; carries exploration_start_timestamp.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ExplorationStopNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Indicates EXPLORE state termination; stops further timeout or completion events for that mission.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_MapCompletenessQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Polls Grid Map module for map completeness flag:
                                - complete: bool indicating no UNKNOWN cells or walls remain.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapCompletenessIndication</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Map completeness boolean computed by Grid Map (LL--MAP--1.3.6).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--18</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_TimebaseQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Reads current system time or cycle count from scheduler to compute elapsed exploration time.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_CurrentTime</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provides global timestamp in milliseconds or ticks converted to milliseconds.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_EventEnqueue</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Abstract interface to enqueue events into system event queue associated with Mission Control and Return-to-start.
                                Event types: EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>EventQueueConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration for queue depth and event record structure.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Internal state:
                  * exploration_active: bool
                  * exploration_start_time_ms: uint32
                  * completed_event_sent, timeout_event_sent flags.
                - On MC_ExplorationStartNotification:
                  * Set exploration_active = true.
                  * Set exploration_start_time_ms = notification.timestamp or SCHED_CurrentTime.
                  * Reset completed_event_sent and timeout_event_sent to false.
                - On MC_ExplorationStopNotification:
                  * Set exploration_active = false.
                - Each control loop cycle while exploration_active:
                  * Read current time SCHED_CurrentTime.
                  * Compute elapsed_ms = current_time - exploration_start_time_ms.
                  * If not completed_event_sent:
                      - Query map completeness from Grid Map.
                      - If complete == true:
                          * Enqueue EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event into event queue.
                          * completed_event_sent = true.
                  * If not timeout_event_sent and elapsed_ms &gt;= 300000 ms:
                      - Enqueue EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event.
                      - timeout_event_sent = true.
                - When handling FG_RemainingTimeQuery:
                  * Provide ES_RemainingTimeInfo with elapsed_ms and remaining_ms as described.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Checked once per control loop iteration, latency of at most T between a condition (completeness or timeout) becoming true and event generation.
                - Global exploration time limit is enforced with ±T ms accuracy.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - At most one EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event and one EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event per mission.
                - EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT is generated no earlier than 300000 ms after exploration start.
                - EXPLORATION_COMPLETED is generated only when map completeness condition holds (no UNKNOWN cells or walls).
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - None beyond scheduler failures; if scheduler time is not monotonic or wraps without handling, elapsed_ms may be miscomputed, but implementation should use unsigned wrap-safe difference calculation.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.3; LL--MAP--1.3.6; LL--MAP--1.5.1; LL--MAP--1.5.2; LL--MAP--1.5.3;
                LL--EVENT--1.1.1; LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--6</ID>
            <Name>Initialization Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Performs all required hardware and software initialization and signals completion to the rest of the system.
                Responsibilities:
                - Initialize hardware drivers for sensors and motors.
                - Initialize software modules including Grid Map, Pose Estimation, State Machines, Event Queue, and configuration parameters.
                - Set INIT_COMPLETED flag or publish INIT_COMPLETED event when initialization is successfully completed.
                - Expose INIT_COMPLETED status to Mission Control and Exploration Status modules.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--15</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_MotorInit</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Performs motor driver initialization before mission start.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MotorInitStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Result of motor initialization. Must indicate success before INIT_COMPLETED is set.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_SensorInit</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Initializes sensor abstraction layer including configuration of sampling rate and filters.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SensorInitStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Indicates sensor subsystem is ready, used as a precondition to set INIT_COMPLETED.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_MapInit</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Signals Grid Map module to initialize cells and walls to UNKNOWN and start-cell to FREE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MapInitStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Acknowledgement from Grid Map after initializing map data structures.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_COMPLETED</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Flag/event, set once after successful initialization.
                                Mission Control reads this to transition from IDLE to EXPLORE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_InitStatusQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Poll from Mission Control to read INIT_COMPLETED flag.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - During system startup (before starting control loop):
                  * Initialize required hardware and software modules in a defined order (e.g., motors, sensors, grid map, pose estimation, mission control, timers).
                  * Validate their status.
                  * If all succeeded, set INIT_COMPLETED flag = true in shared context accessible to Mission Control and other modules.
                - Once control loop starts, Initialization module does not modify INIT_COMPLETED except to read it if needed for diagnostics.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Initialization runs once at system startup, typically before periodic control loop scheduling begins.
                - INIT_COMPLETED must be set before Mission Control can leave IDLE, but Mission Control will explicitly check this flag every loop cycle.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - INIT_COMPLETED is false until all dependent modules report successful initialization.
                - INIT_COMPLETED, once set to true, is never reset to false until system restart.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Initialization Failure:
                  * If any required module fails to initialize, Initialization module must prevent INIT_COMPLETED from being set and may log error; behaviour beyond this LLR scope.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INIT--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--7</ID>
            <Name>Return-to-Start Service</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provides service to compute and execute a path from current cell to designated start cell after exploration completion or timeout.
                Responsibilities:
                - On invocation from Mission Control, compute path from current robot cell to start cell using Cell-based Path Planner and current grid map.
                - Hand back computed path to Mission Control for execution via Motion Controller.
                - Trigger replanning if path becomes invalid due to new map updates.
                - Report path computation status (success/failure).
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_ReturnPathStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1 and CMP--7 Execution.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_ReturnToStartInvoke</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1. Triggers computation of return path.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_PathRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Similar to MC_PathRequest but specifically for return-to-start:
                                - start_cell: current cell from Pose Estimation
                                - goal_cells: single cell = start cell coordinate
                                - path_type: RETURN_TO_START
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_PathResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Return path or failure, forwarded as RS_ReturnPathStatus to Mission Control.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_StartCellQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Query fixed start cell coordinate from Grid Map module.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_StartCellInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Contains start_cell coordinate (row, col) recorded at initialization.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On MC_ReturnToStartInvoke:
                  * Query current_cell from Pose Estimation.
                  * Query start_cell from Grid Map.
                  * Issue RS_PathRequest to Planner.
                  * On PP_PathResponse:
                     - If SUCCESS: assemble RS_ReturnPathStatus with PATH_COMPUTED and path_cells; send to Mission Control.
                     - If FAILURE_NO_PATH: send RS_ReturnPathStatus with PATH_PLANNING_FAILED.
                - Monitor GM_PathInvalidationEvent via Planner; if active return path is invalidated while executing:
                  * RS may remain passive; Mission Control will request a new return path via new RS invocation; alternatively, RS can proactively notify Mission Control that a new plan is required.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Path computation performed once per RETURN_TO_START entry or when path is invalidated.
                - Given small grid, latency of path computation is one or few control cycles.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Return path starts at current_cell and terminates at start_cell.
                - All cells on return path are FREE and edges do not cross PRESENT walls.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Planning failure as described; results in RS_ReturnPathStatus = PATH_PLANNING_FAILED.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RUN--1.1.1; LL--RUN--1.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.1; LL--PLAN--1.1.4; LL--PLAN--1.1.5; LL--EVENT--1.1.1;
                LL--MAP--1.3.4
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--8</ID>
            <Name>Second Run Planning and Status Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Supports the SECOND_RUN mission state by computing the fastest path from start cell to selected goal region, configuring traversal cost models, and reporting success/failure status.
                Responsibilities:
                - After robot returns to start cell and exploration is complete, request selected goal region from Goal Region module.
                - Configure planner traversal cost parameters so that resulting path approximates minimal physical travel time.
                - Invoke path planner to compute fastest path from start cell to any cell in selected 2x2 goal region.
                - Issue this path to Mission Control for execution.
                - Monitor Motion Controller status and pose to determine second run success or failure.
                - Provide boolean/enum status output upon completion or abort.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_SecondRunPlanStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1 and this component. Indicates whether fastest path was found.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_SecondRunExecutionResult</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1. Reports final second run success or failure.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SecondRunInvoke</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Instruction to begin second-run planning, including start cell and goal region if already selected.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_GoalRegionSelectRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests selection of optimal 2x2 FREE region according to traversal cost metric.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_SelectedGoalRegion</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Selected 2x2 goal region as described in CMP--9.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_CostProfileConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Cost model configuration for fastest path computation:
                                - straight_move_cost_weight favouring higher speed along straight segments.
                                - turn_penalty_weight representing time penalty of direction changes.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_PathRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Path request from start cell to any of cells in goal region, with path_type SECOND_RUN_TO_GOAL.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_PathResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Fastest path or failure; used to fill SR_SecondRunPlanStatus.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_ExecutionMonitor</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Uses MC_PathExecutionStatus from Motion Controller to detect completion or failure of second-run execution.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_PathExecutionStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--4 and CMP--1. Used to determine if path execution reached goal region without collision.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--13</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_PoseQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Queries current cell to confirm arrival in goal region.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_CurrentEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                As in CMP--4; used to determine if robot is in any of goal region cells.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On MC_SecondRunInvoke:
                  * Ensure robot is at start_cell (via Pose Estimation and start cell coordinate from Grid Map).
                  * If goal region not provided:
                      - Issue SR_GoalRegionSelectRequest to Goal Region module.
                      - Receive GR_SelectedGoalRegion; store region_cells.
                  * Configure planner cost profile via SR_CostProfileConfig to approximate real travel time:
                      - straight_move_cost ∝ nominal time to traverse one cell at second-run speed.
                      - turn_penalty &gt;= straight_move_cost to penalize excessive turning.
                  * Issue SR_PathRequest to Planner with start_cell and region_cells.
                  * On PP_PathResponse:
                      - If SUCCESS: SR_SecondRunPlanStatus.status = FASTEST_PATH_COMPUTED; pass path to Mission Control for execution via MC_MotionCommand (SECOND_RUN_FAST profile).
                      - If FAILURE_NO_PATH: SR_SecondRunPlanStatus.status = GOAL_UNREACHABLE; MC should handle as failure.
                - During SECOND_RUN execution:
                  * Periodically (each control cycle) check MC_PathExecutionStatus and current pose:
                      - If execution_state == COMPLETED and pose current_cell is in goal region AND no emergency stop or collision recorded:
                         set SR_SecondRunExecutionResult.result = SECOND_RUN_SUCCESS.
                      - Else if EMERGENCY_STOP or collision flag or persistent BLOCKED:
                         set SR_SecondRunExecutionResult.result = SECOND_RUN_FAILURE with failure_reason.
                  * Once result is determined, send SR_SecondRunExecutionResult to Mission Control and stop monitoring for current mission.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Path computation is executed once upon SECOND_RUN entry or re-planning triggers.
                - Success/failure detection is executed each control cycle while SECOND_RUN is active.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Second run can only be initiated after exploration completion and return-to-start completion.
                - Second-run status output (success/failure) is stored and not altered after COMPLETED state.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No fastest path: planner cannot find path to goal region; SR_SecondRunPlanStatus indicates GOAL_UNREACHABLE and SR_SecondRunExecutionResult will indicate failure.
                - Collision or emergency stop during second run: flagged as SECOND_RUN_FAILURE.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RUN--1.2.1; LL--RUN--1.2.2; LL--RUN--1.2.3; LL--RUN--1.2.4; LL--RUN--1.2.5;
                LL--PLAN--1.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.3; LL--ENV--3.1.1; LL--ENV--3.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--9</ID>
            <Name>Goal Region Identification and Selection</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Identifies candidate 2x2 FREE goal regions in grid map and selects the region minimizing path cost from start cell.
                Responsibilities:
                - Scan grid map after exploration completion to find all contiguous 2x2 blocks of FREE cells reachable from start cell.
                - Query path planner to compute minimal path cost from start cell to each candidate region (any of its 4 cells).
                - Select region with minimal traversal cost as maze goal region.
                - Provide selected region to second-run planning and Mission Control.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_MapQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Queries grid map for cell states and start cell coordinate:
                                - get_cell_state
                                - get_start_cell
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_CellStateSnapshot</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Data structure of grid map classifications used to find 2x2 FREE regions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_PathCostRequests</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Reuses planner interface to compute path cost from start to each candidate 2x2 region.
                                For each region, goal_cells = its 4 FREE cells.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_PathResponse</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provides minimal path cost to each region; may use simplified interface where only total_cost is needed.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--8</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_SelectedGoalRegion</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Selected 2x2 region: list of up to 4 (row, col) cells, plus base corner index.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SR_GoalRegionSelectRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request from second-run planning to identify and select goal region.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On SR_GoalRegionSelectRequest or after exploration completion:
                  * Create list of candidate 2x2 regions:
                      for r in 0..(rows-2):
                        for c in 0..(cols-2):
                          if cells (r,c), (r+1,c), (r,c+1), (r+1,c+1) are all FREE:
                              add region candidate with these 4 cells.
                  * For each candidate region:
                      - Use planner to find minimal path cost from start_cell to any of region's 4 cells.
                      - Record minimal cost; discard regions unreachable (planning failure).
                  * Select region with smallest total_cost; break ties using e.g. lexicographic (r,c).
                  * Return selected region to caller.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Candidate identification is performed after map is static (exploration complete), one-time per mission.
                - Number of candidate 2x2 regions is limited (≤ 3x7=21), so interaction with planner is performant.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - All returned goal regions consist of 4 FREE cells.
                - Selected region is reachable from start_cell.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - No valid 2x2 FREE, reachable regions found: module may report failure to second-run planning, which treats this as mission failure or uses fallback.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--ENV--3.1.1; LL--ENV--3.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.1; LL--PLAN--1.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.3; LL--MAP--1.3.6
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--10</ID>
            <Name>Grid Map Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Maintains in-memory representation of the 4x8 maze, including cell and inter-cell wall classifications, start cell, and completeness indication.
                Provides an access interface for other modules with query/update and classification-change notifications, while ensuring single-threaded access within the periodic control loop.
                Responsibilities:
                - Allocate and initialize grid data structure for cells and walls with coordinates aligned to maze geometry.
                - Provide enumeration types and safe transitions for cell states {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED} and wall states {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}.
                - Initialize all cells and walls to UNKNOWN, then set start cell to FREE and record start cell coordinate.
                - Update cells and walls based on mapping input while enforcing Static Map Assumption (no reversion or conflicting transitions).
                - Maintain map completeness flag and provide boolean indication.
                - Implement event mechanism for classification-change notifications.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapUpdateFromSensors</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Mapping module sends processed sensor-derived updates to cell and wall classifications:
                                - mark cell as FREE when traversed without collision.
                                - mark wall segments PRESENT or ABSENT from detection algorithms.
                                Grid Map validates and applies these updates.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_CellWallUpdateRequests</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Requests to update classification of specific cell or wall segments.
                                Each request includes:
                                - target type: CELL or WALL
                                - coordinates (row,col[,orientation])
                                - new_state enumeration.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--2</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_ClassificationChangeNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--2. Emitted when certain cells or walls change from UNKNOWN to specific states.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>FG_MapQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--2. Frontier Generation queries cell classification and neighbours via this interface.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_PathInvalidationEvent</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--3. Emitted when previously UNKNOWN cells/walls along active path become BLOCKED/PRESENT.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_MapQueries</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--3. Planner queries map for cell and wall states.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--5</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapCompletenessIndication</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Boolean flag indicating map completeness: no UNKNOWN cells or walls.
                                Provided on ES_MapCompletenessQuery or updated each time cell or wall state transitions from UNKNOWN.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>ES_MapCompletenessQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--5. Exploration-Status queries map completeness.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--7</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_StartCellInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provides stored start_cell coordinate for Return-to-start Service.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RS_StartCellQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--7. Return-to-start service queries start cell.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--9</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_CellStateSnapshot</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Snapshot of cell states to detect 2x2 FREE regions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GR_MapQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--9. Goal Region module queries cell states.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--6</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MapInitStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Indicates that map data structure and start cell initialization are complete.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>INIT_MapInit</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--6. Initialization module triggers map initialization.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Data structures:
                  * cell_state[ROWS][COLS]: enumeration {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}.
                  * wall_state_vertical[ROWS][COLS+1]: walls between horizontally adjacent cells and boundaries.
                  * wall_state_horizontal[ROWS+1][COLS]: walls between vertically adjacent cells and boundaries.
                  * start_cell: (row, col).
                  * map_complete: bool.
                - Initialization (on INIT_MapInit):
                  * Set all cell_state[r][c] = UNKNOWN.
                  * Set all wall_state arrays to UNKNOWN.
                  * Set start_cell to fixed coordinate (e.g. row 0, column 0).
                  * Set cell_state[start_cell] = FREE.
                  * Recompute map_complete flag (false).
                - Updates:
                  * On MP_CellWallUpdateRequests:
                    - For cell update:
                        if current state is UNKNOWN and new_state in {FREE, BLOCKED}:
                           set cell_state; record that classification changed.
                        else if current state equals new_state: ignore (idempotent).
                        else: ignore or log violation (Static Map Assumption forbids other transitions).
                    - For wall update:
                        if current wall_state is UNKNOWN and new_state in {PRESENT, ABSENT}:
                           set wall_state.
                        else if current equals new_state: ignore.
                        else: ignore/log.
                    - For each update causing UNKNOWN -&gt; known transition:
                        - Notify registered listeners (Frontier Generation, Planner (for invalidation), etc.).
                        - Recompute map_complete flag if necessary.
                  * Map complete computation:
                    - After each update, optionally maintain counts of UNKNOWN cells and walls; map_complete = (unknown_cell_count == 0 and unknown_wall_count == 0).
                - Access Interface:
                  * get_cell_state, set_cell_state, get_wall_state, set_wall_state, get_start_cell, get_map_complete.
                  * Register classification-change callbacks (modules may provide filter on types of changes).
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - All operations occur in context of periodic control loop to guarantee single-threaded access.
                - Grid is small; a full completeness computation or iterate over all cells/walls is safe within one cycle.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Each cell is always in exactly one of {UNKNOWN, FREE, BLOCKED}.
                - Transitions:
                    * UNKNOWN -&gt; FREE or UNKNOWN -&gt; BLOCKED only, no reversion to UNKNOWN.
                - Each wall segment is always in exactly one of {UNKNOWN, PRESENT, ABSENT}.
                - Wall transitions:
                    * UNKNOWN -&gt; PRESENT or UNKNOWN -&gt; ABSENT only, no reversion to UNKNOWN or switching PRESENT↔ABSENT.
                - map_complete is TRUE iff all cells and walls are non-UNKNOWN.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Misuse of interface attempting forbidden state changes is rejected and may be logged but does not corrupt map.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.3.1; LL--MAP--1.3.2; LL--MAP--1.3.3; LL--MAP--1.3.4; LL--MAP--1.3.5; LL--MAP--1.3.6; LL--MAP--1.3.7;
                LL--MAP--1.4.1; LL--MAP--1.4.2; LL--MAP--1.4.3; LL--MAP--1.4.4; LL--ENV--1.1.1; LL--ENV--1.4.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--11</ID>
            <Name>Sensor Abstraction and Filtering Layer</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Wraps hardware-specific ultrasonic and infrared sensor functions to provide normalized, filtered, and validated sensor data to higher-level modules.
                Responsibilities:
                - Sample ultrasonic_get_distance() and infrared_get_dsl_status()/infrared_get_dsr_status() at a configurable rate equal to the control loop frequency.
                - Represent ultrasonic measurement as (distance_cm, timestamp, valid_flag) and IR as (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp, valid_flag).
                - Apply temporal filtering (moving-average or median) to raw sensor data to reduce random noise.
                - Apply hysteresis/thresholding for wall detection to prevent classification flip-flopping.
                - Detect invalid or out-of-range readings and replace with safe defaults or mark as invalid.
                - Provide processed sensor data to mapping, motion control, and mission control.
                - Incorporate ultrasonic uncertainty interval (±12 cm) into data used for collision risk and wall detection.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--18</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_SamplingSchedule</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configured sampling rate [10,50] Hz and linking of sampling to control loop iterations.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_LoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Control loop tick; SAL uses this to sample sensors once per iteration.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--15</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_UltrasonicDriverCalls</Name>
                            <Description>
                                SAL calls ultrasonic_get_distance() hardware API.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_IRDriverCalls</Name>
                            <Description>
                                SAL calls infrared_get_dsl_status() and infrared_get_dsr_status() hardware APIs.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>UltrasonicRawData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Raw float distance from ultrasonic sensor representing cm to nearest obstacle, possibly including sentinel values for invalid readings.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>IRRawStatus</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Raw uint8_t statuses from left and right IR sensors representing obstacle flags.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--13</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_PoseAlignmentQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Query for current heading to determine if robot is aligned to maze axes within 10 degrees for side wall detection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_HeadingEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Discrete heading and potentially continuous yaw used to check alignment tolerance for IR-based wall detection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_ToMapping</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Processed sensor data forwarded to Mapping module for wall and cell updates.
                                Contains:
                                - filtered ultrasonic distance with uncertainty interval
                                - IR obstacle flags with alignment information.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MapSensorConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration including thresholds and hysteresis parameters specific to mapping functions.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_SensorSnapshot</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Single, combined sensor measurement structure provided each control cycle:
                                - ultrasonic: (distance_cm, timestamp, valid_flag)
                                - infrared: (left_flag, right_flag, timestamp, valid_flag).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SensorAvailabilityQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--1. Mission Control queries this snapshot to ensure valid data are available before starting EXPLORE.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--4. Provided every loop for collision avoidance and wall avoidance manoeuvres.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_SensorUseRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Notifies SAL that Motion Controller consumes current filtered data each cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Sampling:
                  * On each SCHED_LoopTick:
                    - Call ultrasonic_get_distance(); obtain raw floating-point distance.
                    - Call infrared_get_dsl_status(), infrared_get_dsr_status(); obtain raw flags.
                - Invalid Reading Handling:
                  * For ultrasonic:
                      - If returned value is negative, NaN, or equals sentinel such as 0 or &gt;= maximum measurable distance, set valid_flag = false and either:
                         * set distance_cm to a safe large default (e.g. max_range_cm), or
                         * mark measurement as invalid for mapping decisions.
                  * For IR:
                      - Validate raw status codes; if out-of-range, treat as no obstacle (false) with valid_flag=true or mark invalid based on design.
                - Filtering:
                  * Maintain sliding window buffers of last N_u ultrasonic samples and N_ir IR samples (N configurable, e.g. 3..5).
                  * Apply moving median or average to ultrasonic distances to produce filtered distance.
                  * For IR, apply simple debouncing/hysteresis: require K consecutive "obstacle" readings before left_flag/right_flag changes from 0 to 1, and K consecutive "no obstacle" before 1 to 0.
                - Wall Proximity Thresholding:
                  * Compare filtered ultrasonic distance against configurable thresholds:
                      - d_wall_detect: threshold below which presence of wall is inferred.
                      - d_free_detect: threshold above which free space is inferred.
                    Use hysteresis between these thresholds to prevent flip-flopping.
                - Uncertainty Model:
                  * Represent ultrasonic measurement as interval [d-12cm, d+12cm].
                  * Provide this interval as part of SAL_FilteredSensorData for collision risk and front wall detection.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Sampling and filtering occur exactly once per control loop iteration at rate in [10,50] Hz as configured by Reliability module.
                - Sensor reading, filtering, and derivative updates must complete within one control loop cycle.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - SAL delivers exactly one consolidated sensor snapshot per control cycle.
                - Filtered values never depend on samples older than configured buffer size.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Persistent invalid sensor readings (e.g. ultrasonic failure) should be flagged via valid_flag=false and logged; modules using SAL data must treat invalid readings conservatively (e.g. assume no new walls but rely on existing map).
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--1.1.1; LL--INTERF--1.1.2; LL--INTERF--2.1.1; LL--INTERF--3.1.1;
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1; LL--INTERF--3.3.1; LL--INTERF--3.4.1;
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1; LL--RELIAB--1.2.2; LL--MAP--1.2.1; LL--MAP--1.2.2; LL--MAP--1.2.3
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--12</ID>
            <Name>Mapping and Wall Detection Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Uses processed sensor data and pose estimation to update grid map cells and walls, detect front and side walls, and confirm cell free/blocked status.
                Responsibilities:
                - When robot is at or between cell centers, interpret ultrasonic and IR readings to detect presence of walls and free space.
                - For front wall detection:
                  * interpret ultrasonic measurement interval [d-12,d+12] against expected robot-center-to-wall distance based on cell geometry and robot size.
                - For side wall detection:
                  * interpret IR obstacle indications as side walls when robot is aligned to maze axes within ≤10°.
                - Apply consistency checks (N consecutive readings) before changing established FREE/ABSENT classifications.
                - Mark cells as FREE when traversed without collision and consistent with sensor data; infer BLOCKED cells behind PRESENT walls.
                - Use pose alignment and known map features to correct pose estimations.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_SensorDataConsumption</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Consumes SAL_FilteredSensorData each loop for mapping.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_FilteredSensorData</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--11. Mapping uses this to infer cell and wall states.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--13</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_PoseQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Retrieve current cell, heading, and continuous position to determine whether robot is at a cell center or between cells.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_CurrentEstimate</Name>
                            <Description>
                                As before; plus optionally metrics indicating progress along current cell transition, used for when to apply updates.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_CellWallUpdateRequests</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--10. Mapping sends intended changes:
                                - wall PRESENT or ABSENT on faces around current cell.
                                - cell FREE when traversed successfully or BLOCKED for inferred neighbours across PRESENT walls.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_PoseCorrectionInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Mapping uses map features (known walls and cell boundaries) to suggest pose corrections to Pose Estimation.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapQueries</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Not previously defined but inferred; Mapping queries map to know existing cell and wall states.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--14</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_GeometricParamsQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Queries robot footprint radius and environment cell &amp; wall dimensions to compute expected sensor distances.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GeomParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Includes:
                                - cell_size_cm ~17.2
                                - robot_radius_cm = 5.5
                                - wall_thickness_cm = 1.6
                                - IR effective range ~4 cm
                                - IR mounting angle ~25°
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Each control loop cycle, for each sample where pose is at cell center or during transition:
                  * Front wall detection (LL--MAP--1.2.1):
                      - Compute expected nominal distance from robot center to front wall for the current cell and heading, given cell_size and robot_radius.
                      - Accept ultrasonic measurement d as front wall if interval [d-12, d+12] intersects expected distance interval [d_expected_min, d_expected_max].
                      - Map this detection to a specific wall segment in grid map (horizontal or vertical).
                  * Side wall detection from IR (LL--MAP--1.2.2, 1.2.3, 1.2.4, 1.2.5):
                      - Check alignment to maze axes; if absolute heading error ≤ 10°:
                         - If left_flag is active, treat as wall along left side of current cell at nominal distance ~4cm from sensor, compensated for IR mounting angle per LL--INTERF--3.4.1.
                         - Similarly for right_flag.
                      - Convert these into wall segment coordinates (relative to cell and heading).
                  * Wall proximity thresholding and hysteresis (LL--MAP--1.2.3, LL--RELIAB--1.2.1):
                      - Use filtered and debounced sensor data.
                      - Only change wall classification when detection is stable across at least N consecutive readings where N≥2 and default 3 (LL--RELIAB--1.2.2).
                  * Free cell confirmation (LL--MAP--1.4.3):
                      - When Pose Estimation signals that robot successfully entered a new cell center without collisions on entry face and with no contradictory sensor evidence:
                         - Mark that cell as FREE, if not previously classified.
                  * Blocked cell inference (LL--MAP--1.4.4):
                      - When a wall segment between current cell and neighbour cell is classified as PRESENT:
                         - Mark neighbour cell as BLOCKED.
                         - Ensure Motion Controller will never command entry into that cell.
                  * Pose correction using map features (LL--POSE--1.1.2):
                      - When walls detected match expected positions of known cell boundaries and robot is nearly aligned:
                         - Provide Pose Correction Info to pose module: snap heading to nearest axis, adjust position to nearest cell center consistent with wall configuration.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Executed once per control loop after SAL data acquisition and before Grid Map update and Mission Control.
                - Must complete detection and update requests within single loop cycle.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Mapping never directly violates static map assumptions; all updates from UNKNOWN to FREE/BLOCKED (cells) or PRESENT/ABSENT (walls) only, enforced by Grid Map module.
                - Cell FREE is only set when traversal is successful and sensor data is consistent (per N consecutive reading policy).
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Contradictory sensor vs. map evidence (e.g., sensors detect a wall where map says FREE/ABSENT) is resolved via consistency checks (N &gt;=2 consecutive readings required to change classification).
                - Persistent inconsistencies may be logged and may lead to emergency behaviours defined elsewhere; mapping itself remains conservative about state changes.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.1; LL--MAP--1.2.2; LL--MAP--1.2.3; LL--MAP--1.2.4;
                LL--MAP--1.3.2; LL--MAP--1.4.3; LL--MAP--1.4.4;
                LL--RELIAB--1.2.1; LL--RELIAB--1.2.2;
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1; LL--INTERF--3.3.1; LL--INTERF--3.4.1;
                LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1; LL--ENV--1.2.1; LL--ENV--1.3.1; LL--ENV--1.4.1; LL--POSE--1.1.2; LL--POSE--1.1.3
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--13</ID>
            <Name>Pose Estimation Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Estimates robot pose at cell-level granularity and supports correction using map features for drift mitigation.
                Responsibilities:
                - Maintain estimate of current maze cell index (row, col) and discrete heading aligned with maze axes.
                - Update pose each control loop by integrating differential drive kinematics over period T or measured cycle duration and issued motor commands.
                - Detect transitions between cell centers and notify mapping subsystem.
                - Correct pose when map-based alignment conditions are met.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--14</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_KinematicParamsRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Queries differential drive kinematic parameters and mapping from motor_set speeds to linear/angular velocities.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>DD_KinematicParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                As in CMP--4; includes wheel-base, wheel-radius, and calibration constants.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--15</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_MotorCommandLog</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Access to last motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) commands (velocity surrogates) to integrate motion.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MotorCommandHistory</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Sequence or last commands used per cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--18</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_LoopPeriodQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Reads control-loop period T or measured cycle duration.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_LoopPeriod</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Specifies T, used for integration.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_CellCenterEntryNotification</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See LL--POSE--1.1.3: notifies mapping when pose crosses from one cell center to adjacent.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_MapQueries</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optionally used to ensure cell indices remain within map boundaries.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--12</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_CorrectionApply</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Pose module receives PoseCorrectionInfo from mapping to snap heading and position.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_PoseCorrectionInfo</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Includes new discrete heading and corrected cell center coordinates.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Internal representation:
                  * Continuous pose: (x, y, theta) relative to maze reference frame, where cell centers are spaced at 17.2cm.
                  * Discrete cell index: row = round(y / cell_size), col = round(x / cell_size).
                  * Discrete heading: nearest axis-aligned orientation (N,E,S,W) derived from theta.
                - Per control loop:
                  * Integrate kinematics using last motor_set speeds and T:
                      - Compute linear velocities v_left, v_right from speed settings and calibration.
                      - Compute v_linear, omega from differential drive equations.
                      - Update x,y,theta via forward integration.
                  * Derive new cell index and heading; if indices differ from previous cell center and robot has passed appropriate distance threshold ~ cell_size/2 since last center:
                      - Register cell center crossing; send POSE_CellCenterEntryNotification with new cell indices to Mapping module.
                  * Apply corrections:
                      - When MP_PoseCorrectionInfo is received and conditions are met (e.g. robot near a cell center):
                          - Set theta to nearest multiple of 90° as indicated.
                          - Snap x,y to cell center coordinates computed from (row,col).
                - Provide pose to other modules via POSE_CurrentEstimate.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Updated once per control loop cycle using measured cycle duration.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Discrete heading remains one of {N,E,S,W}.
                - Cell indices remain within [0,3]x[0,7] for 4x8 maze.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - If integration drifts beyond acceptable thresholds without alignment corrections, mapping and motion control may degrade; map-based corrections reduce this risk.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--POSE--1.1.1; LL--POSE--1.1.2; LL--POSE--1.1.3;
                LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1; LL--ENV--1.2.1; LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--14</ID>
            <Name>Kinematic and Geometry Parameters</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Encapsulates knowledge of robot differential drive kinematics, footprint, and maze geometry parameters that influence collision checking, motion primitives, and sensor interpretation.
                Responsibilities:
                - Provide robot footprint model (circle radius 5.5 cm) for collision checks.
                - Provide differential drive kinematic equations for mapping motor_set speeds to pose changes.
                - Provide cell dimension (17.2 cm) and wall thickness (1.6 cm) for transformation between physical space and grid indices.
                - Provide IR range and orientation for lateral wall position computation.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>DD_KinematicParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--4. Contains:
                                - wheel_base_cm
                                - wheel_radius_cm equivalent or mapping function from speed units to cm/s
                                - relation between motor_set speed [0..100] and physical velocity.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GeomParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--12. Contains cell_size_cm, robot_radius_cm, wall_thickness_cm.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_KinematicParamsQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                From Motion Controller or Pose Estimation, requesting the above parameters.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Provides static configuration values at initialization and may allow compile-time or configuration-time changes but no dynamic behaviour after startup.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Reads/writes only when queried; no periodic execution.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Robot radius remains 5.5cm.
                - Cell size remains 17.2cm for relations between distance and cell transitions.
                - Wall thickness remains 1.6cm for collision modelling.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Incorrect parameters may compromise safety or performance; must be validated prior to deployment.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1; LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1; LL--HARDWARE--2.1.2;
                LL--ENV--1.2.1; LL--ENV--1.3.1; LL--ENV--1.4.1; LL--INTERF--3.3.1; LL--INTERF--3.4.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--15</ID>
            <Name>Motor Command Interface</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provides controlled access to motor_set(left_speed, right_speed) hardware function and integrates it with control loop.
                Responsibilities:
                - Enforce the constraints: motor_set is the exclusive method to control differential drive motors, speeds in [0,100], invoked at most once per control loop cycle.
                - Provide calibration parameters mapping between command units and physical speeds.
                - Expose last command history for pose estimation.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MotorCommandExecution</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Executes motor_set for requested left/right speeds from Motion Controller.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotorSet</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--4. Contains target speeds.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_DriverAccess</Name>
                            <Description>
                                SAL may use hardware API wrappers defined here; not critical for path planning but ensures consistent hardware access.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SensorDriverConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Configuration linking SAL to underlying hardware.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On each control loop cycle:
                  * Accept at most one MC_MotorSet request; check bounds and issue underlying hardware call motor_set(left_speed, right_speed).
                  * Record last_command for Pose Estimation.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Called once per loop cycle when there is a new command.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - left_speed,right_speed ∈ [0,100].
                - motor_set is not called more than once per T.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Underlying hardware errors are outside this scope; interface may log and propagate minimal info.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--INTERF--1.2.1; LL--HARDWARE--2.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--16</ID>
            <Name>Reliability and Safety Constraints Module</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Centralizes safety-related parameters (minimum clearance, emergency stop, speed limitation, consistency thresholds) and ensures they are honoured by dependent modules.
                Responsibilities:
                - Provide configurable minimum clearance margin M &gt; 0 cm based on ultrasonic uncertainty and pose/wall localization errors.
                - Enforce emergency stop on imminent collision by commanding 0 speed and requiring new safe trajectory before motion resumes.
                - Define maximum safe translational speed based on sensor sampling rate, emergency stop distance, and ultrasonic uncertainty.
                - Provide sensor-consistency parameters (N consecutive readings) used by mapping.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RE_SafetyLimits</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--4. Contains:
                                - emergency_distance_cm
                                - min_clearance_margin_cm M
                                - max_safe_speed_cm_s based on SAL's sampling rate and ultrasonic uncertainty.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RE_EmergencyStopCommand</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional interface to instruct Motion Controller or Motor Interface to immediately stop on high-level detection.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_CollisionRiskReport</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Reports from Motion Controller about near collisions; may influence dynamic adjustment of safety parameters.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RE_SensorSamplingConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Defines sampling rate in [10,50] Hz and acceptable jitter range.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_SamplingCapabilities</Name>
                            <Description>
                                SAL reports its supported ranges; RE selects an appropriate default (e.g. 20 Hz).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--12</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RE_ConsistencyParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Parameter N (2 ≤ N ≤ 10, default 3) specifying required consecutive sensor readings to reverse established FREE/ABSENT classification.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_ConsistencyConfigRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Request from mapping for current N.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--14</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>RE_ClearanceComputationConfig</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Using robot footprint, ultrasonic uncertainty, and geometry, RE computes minimal distances for safe standoff.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GeomParams</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--14, used in safety calculations.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - On initialization:
                  * Select sensor sampling rate f ∈ [10,50] Hz (default 20Hz).
                  * Given f, T=1/f, emergency stop distance threshold, maximum braking capability, and ultrasonic uncertainty ±12cm:
                      - Compute maximum safe translational speed such that robot can detect a wall at distance d and stop before hitting it with margin M.
                - Provide these parameters to dependent modules above.
                - Provide N (consecutive readings) to mapping.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - Safety parameters are computed at initialization and updated rarely, if at all.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - M &gt; 0 cm.
                - 2 ≤ N ≤ 10; default N=3 documented.
                - Sampling rate remains within [10,50] Hz.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Undersized M or overspeed misconfiguration can degrade safety; robust configuration management is required.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1; LL--RELIAB--1.1.2; LL--RELIAB--1.2.1; LL--RELIAB--1.2.2;
                LL--INTERF--2.3.1; LL--HARDWARE--2.3.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--17</ID>
            <Name>Environment Grid Coordinate System</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Defines coordinate system for mapping between physical maze positions and grid indices used across mapping, planning, and control modules.
                Responsibilities:
                - Provide 4x8 grid with consistent mapping from physical positions to (row, col) indices.
                - Define start cell coordinate convention (e.g. row=0, col=0).
                - Provide functions to convert between (x,y) positions and cell indices using cell size.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--10</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Env_GridDefinition</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Defines that grid map has 4 rows and 8 columns; row index increases e.g. north-to-south, column index west-to-east, with (0,0) as start cell.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>GM_GridQuery</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Internal; grid map queries environment module to confirm grid dimension assumptions if required.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--13</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>Env_CellIndexConversion</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Provide functions:
                                - (row,col) = world_to_grid(x,y)
                                - (x,y) = grid_to_world(row,col).
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>POSE_ConversionRequest</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Pose Estimation may request conversion when mapping continuous to discrete coordinates.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Stateless conversions using cell size and origin assumptions.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - On-demand.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Maze dimension is fixed to 4 rows, 8 columns.
                - Start cell coordinate remains constant.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - None beyond configuration mismatches; must be consistent with physical maze.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--ENV--1.1.1; LL--MAP--1.3.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>

        <Component>
            <ID>CMP--18</ID>
            <Name>Periodic Control Loop Scheduler</Name>
            <Purpose>
                Provides periodic control loop with period T and ensures required execution sequence of sensor acquisition, mapping, mission control, planning, and motor command issuance.
                Responsibilities:
                - Implement periodic control loop with configurable T such that frequency equals sensor sampling rate.
                - On each iteration:
                  (1) Acquire sensor readings via SAL.
                  (2) Update grid map using Mapping module.
                  (3) Update Mission Control state machine.
                  (4) Compute/update current path as required by active state.
                  (5) Issue motor_set via Motion Controller and Motor Interface.
                - Provide measured cycle time or fixed period T to Pose Estimation and other time-based computations.
            </Purpose>
            <ConnectedComponents>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--11</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_LoopTick</Name>
                            <Description>
                                See CMP--11. Triggers SAL sampling each cycle.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SAL_SamplingSchedule</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Sampling configuration from Reliability module; used to set loop frequency.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--12</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MappingStepTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Triggers Mapping module processing sequence after SAL.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MP_MappingDoneAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional ack from Mapping module; ensures mapping finishes before state machine update.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--1</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MissionControlStepTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Ensures Mission Control is executed after mapping but before path planning and motor commands.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_StepDoneAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional ack from Mission Control.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--3</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_PlannerTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional signal to Planner for path computations due in the current iteration; may be integrated directly in Mission Control or Motion Controller steps.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>PP_StepDoneAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional ack from Planner.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
                <ConnectedComponent>
                    <Identifier>CMP--4</Identifier>
                    <Transmit>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>SCHED_MotionControlTrigger</Name>
                            <Description>
                                At end of each loop iteration, Motion Controller is triggered to compute and send MC_MotorSet command.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Transmit>
                    <Receive>
                        <Signal>
                            <Name>MC_MotionDoneAck</Name>
                            <Description>
                                Optional ack from Motion Controller.
                            </Description>
                        </Signal>
                    </Receive>
                </ConnectedComponent>
            </ConnectedComponents>
            <Execution>
                - Control loop (repeats indefinitely until mission end):
                  while true:
                    - timestamp_start = current_time()
                    - Trigger SAL sampling (SCHED_LoopTick).
                    - Execute Mapping step (wall/cell updates, pose corrections).
                    - Execute Mission Control FSM step (CMP--1).
                    - Execute necessary planning steps (if MC requested).
                    - Execute Motion Control step including motor_set.
                    - Sleep until next cycle such that total period ≈ T; measure actual elapsed and provide to Pose Estimation.
                - Provide SCHED_LoopPeriod and SCHED_CurrentTime to modules needing timing.
            </Execution>
            <Timing>
                - T configured from Reliability module; sensor sampling rate = 1/T ∈ [10,50] Hz.
                - Timing jitter is bounded by tolerance specified elsewhere; scheduler will aim to minimize jitter.
            </Timing>
            <Invariants>
                - Sequence of operations per cycle is always SAL -&gt; Mapping -&gt; Mission Control -&gt; Planning -&gt; Motion.
                - Motor command issuance always occurs once per cycle at the end.
            </Invariants>
            <Failures>
                - Excessive jitter or missed cycles may degrade performance; must be monitored by platform but outside this design.
            </Failures>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--SCHED--1.1.1; LL--RELIAB--1.2.1; LL--INTERF--1.1.1; LL--INTERF--1.2.1; LL--MAP--1.1.2; LL--PLAN--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Component>
    </Components>

    <StateMachines version="1">
        <StateMachine>
            <ID>FSM--1</ID>
            <OfComponent>CMP--1</OfComponent>
            <States>
                <State>
                    <Name>IDLE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Monitor INIT_COMPLETED flag.
                        - Monitor SAL_SensorSnapshot.valid_flag values.
                        - Do not issue movement commands.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>EXPLORE</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - If no active exploration path, request frontier set and select target frontier.
                        - Request path to selected frontier and command Motion Controller to execute with exploration speed.
                        - Monitor exploration events (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED, EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT).
                        - Monitor path execution status; trigger replanning on BLOCKED/EMERGENCY_STOP or map updates.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>RETURN_TO_START</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Invoke Return-to-start Service to compute path back to start cell.
                        - Command Motion Controller to execute return path.
                        - Monitor execution progress, replanning if invalidated.
                        - On reach start cell or planning failure, prepare for SECOND_RUN or COMPLETED.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>SECOND_RUN</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Request/confirm goal region selection.
                        - Configure planner for fastest path.
                        - Command Motion Controller to execute fastest path with higher speed profile.
                        - Monitor success/failure conditions (arrival at goal region, collisions).
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
                <State>
                    <Name>COMPLETED</Name>
                    <StateAction>
                        - Cease issuing new motion commands.
                        - Maintain final second-run status for external reporting.
                    </StateAction>
                </State>
            </States>
            <Transitions>
                <Transition>
                    <From>IDLE</From>
                    <To>EXPLORE</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        INIT_COMPLETED flag set by Initialization module AND at least one valid set of ultrasonic and infrared sensor measurements available from SAL in the current or a previous control loop iteration.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Mission has not yet started (first transition from IDLE).
                        - No fault condition inhibiting exploration is active.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Set exploration start timestamp by sending MC_ExplorationStartNotification to Exploration-Status module.
                        - Initialize internal exploration counters and flags.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EXPLORE</From>
                    <To>RETURN_TO_START</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event dequeued from system event queue OR EXPLORATION_TIMEOUT event dequeued; whichever occurs first.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Event has not already been consumed for this mission.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Send MC_ExplorationStopNotification to Exploration-Status module.
                        - Invoke Return-to-start Service with trigger_source according to event type.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>SECOND_RUN</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Return path execution completed successfully (Motion Controller reports execution_state == COMPLETED and current_cell == start_cell).
                        - Exploration previously declared complete (EXPLORATION_COMPLETED event had occurred, not timeout-only).
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - No planning failure occurred for return path.
                        - Exploration status indicates map completeness.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Initiate Second-run planning via MC_SecondRunInvoke.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>RETURN_TO_START</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Return path planning failure (RS_ReturnPathStatus PATH_PLANNING_FAILED), OR
                        - Execution cannot reach start cell due to repeated BLOCKED/EMERGENCY_STOP and no alternative paths.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - Replanning attempts exhausted or explicitly limited by configuration.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Set mission final status to failure.
                        - Issue STOP command to Motion Controller to ensure motors are halted.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>SECOND_RUN</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        - Second-run execution result becomes available from Second-run Planning module indicating success or failure.
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - SECOND_RUN path planning has been attempted.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Store final second-run status (success or failure).
                        - If needed, issue STOP to Motion Controller.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
                <Transition>
                    <From>EXPLORE</From>
                    <To>COMPLETED</To>
                    <Trigger>
                        Optional direct mission abort if unrecoverable system fault occurs during exploration (e.g. hardware failure).
                    </Trigger>
                    <Guard>
                        - System fault flag set.
                    </Guard>
                    <TransitionAction>
                        - Stop all motion; set mission status to failure.
                    </TransitionAction>
                </Transition>
            </Transitions>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.1.1; LL--MAP--1.1.2; LL--MAP--1.1.3; LL--MAP--1.5.1; LL--RUN--1.1.1; LL--RUN--1.2.1;
                LL--RUN--1.2.4; LL--RUN--1.2.5; LL--EVENT--1.1.1; LL--INIT--1.1.1; LL--SCHED--1.1.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </StateMachine>
    </StateMachines>

    <AdditionalData version="1">
        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--1</ID>
            <Content>
                Enumeration Definitions

                CellState (for grid cells):
                - UNKNOWN: cell not yet explored; default after initialization.
                - FREE: robot has successfully traversed into cell without collision and sensor data are consistent; used as traversable nodes in path planner.
                - BLOCKED: inferred obstacle cell not to be entered; path planner and motion controller treat as non-traversable.

                WallState (for inter-cell walls):
                - UNKNOWN: wall presence/absence not yet observed.
                - PRESENT: wall detected between adjacent cells; movement across this boundary must not be commanded.
                - ABSENT: no wall between cells; movement allowed for FREE cells.

                MissionState (for Mission Control FSM):
                - IDLE
                - EXPLORE
                - RETURN_TO_START
                - SECOND_RUN
                - COMPLETED

                PathRequestType:
                - EXPLORATION_TO_FRONTIER
                - RETURN_TO_START
                - SECOND_RUN_TO_GOAL

                PlannerStatus:
                - SUCCESS
                - FAILURE_NO_PATH

                ExecutionState (for path execution status):
                - IDLE
                - EXECUTING
                - BLOCKED
                - COMPLETED
                - EMERGENCY_STOP

                SecondRunResult:
                - SECOND_RUN_SUCCESS
                - SECOND_RUN_FAILURE
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.4.1; LL--MAP--1.4.2; LL--MAP--1.1.1; LL--PLAN--1.1.1; LL--PLAN--1.1.5;
                LL--RUN--1.2.4; LL--RUN--1.2.5
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>
        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--2</ID>
            <Content>
                Collision and Clearance Geometry

                Environment parameters:
                - cell_size_cm ≈ 17.2 cm (LL--ENV--1.2.1).
                - wall_thickness_cm ≈ 1.6 cm (LL--ENV--1.3.1).
                - robot_radius_cm = 5.5 cm (LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1).
                - min_clearance_margin_cm = M &gt; 0 cm (configurable, from Reliability module, LL--RELIAB--1.1.1).

                For a robot modeled as a circle of radius R moving along a corridor between walls:
                - Minimum distance from robot center to any wall must always be ≥ (R + M).
                - For grid-map-based collision checks:
                    * Represent walls as line segments at cell boundaries.
                    * When robot is at cell center, distance to front wall for a corridor with single cell spacing:
                        d_nominal ≈ (cell_size_cm / 2) - (wall_thickness_cm/2) - robot_radius_cm.
                    * For front wall detection using ultrasonic distance d:
                        - Consider interval [d-12,d+12].
                        - Compare to expected interval [d_nominal - epsilon, d_nominal + epsilon] where epsilon accounts for pose uncertainty.
                        - If intersection non-empty, classify wall as PRESENT.

                Clearance against path:
                - For each candidate motion primitive, approximate swept path of robot circle.
                - Ensure distance from path centerline to any PRESENT wall's geometric line, minus robot_radius, is ≥ M.
                - If not, motion primitive is disallowed for planning and execution.
            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--HARDWARE--1.1.1; LL--ENV--1.2.1; LL--ENV--1.3.1; LL--MAP--1.2.1; LL--MAP--1.2.4;
                LL--RELIAB--1.1.1; LL--INTERF--2.3.1
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>
        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--3</ID>
            <Content>
                Time-Aware Planning Calculations

                Global mapping time limit:
                - Max exploration time T_max = 5 minutes = 300000 ms (LL--MAP--1.5.1).

                Nominal cell traversal duration parameter:
                - Parameter t_cell_ms: nominal time to traverse one cell at exploration speed (LL--MAP--1.5.3).
                - Recommended configuration range based on empirical tests; accessible via Exploration Status module.

                Remaining time estimation:
                - Let t_elapsed_ms be elapsed time since exploration start.
                - Remaining time: t_rem_ms = max(0, T_max - t_elapsed_ms).
                - For a prospective frontier target with path cost C (in edge units) and cost scaling factor k(ms/unit):
                    * Estimated travel time: t_travel_ms = k * C.
                    * Estimated mapping time at target (local exploration) ≈ t_cell_ms.
                    * Combined estimate: t_estimate_ms = t_travel_ms + t_cell_ms.

                Frontier feasibility condition:
                - A frontier target is feasible if t_estimate_ms ≤ t_rem_ms.
                - Frontier selection coarse filtering: discard all targets with t_estimate_ms &gt; t_rem_ms before heuristic evaluation.

                Planner cost profile mapping:
                - For exploration:
                    * Use cost_straight = 1 unit, cost_turn ≥ 1 (e.g. 1.2) and map k_explore = t_cell_ms (per cell) for time approximation.
                - For second run (fastest path):
                    * Choose cost_straight tuned so that path minimizing (number_of_cells * 1 + number_of_turns * turn_penalty) approximates shortest travel time.
                    * Speed profile for second run uses higher translational velocity while ensuring safe stopping per Reliability module.

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.5.1; LL--MAP--1.5.2; LL--MAP--1.5.3; LL--PLAN--1.1.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>
        <Data>
            <ID>DAT--4</ID>
            <Content>
                Sensor Consistency and Hysteresis Configuration

                Consistency parameter N:
                - N is an integer ≥ 2 with default value 3 (LL--RELIAB--1.2.2).
                - Recommended range: 2 ≤ N ≤ 10.
                - When new sensor readings contradict current map classification (e.g., wall indicated where map says ABSENT/FREE), require at least N consecutive contradictory readings before changing classification.

                Wall proximity hysteresis:
                - For ultrasonic readings, define two thresholds:
                  * d_wall_detect_cm: if filtered distance &lt;= d_wall_detect_cm, treat as wall present candidate.
                  * d_free_detect_cm: if filtered distance &gt;= d_free_detect_cm, treat as wall absent candidate.
                  * d_free_detect_cm &gt; d_wall_detect_cm to provide hysteresis.
                - State machine for front wall classification per cell face:
                  * UNKNOWN:
                      - If stable wall indications (duration or consecutive count) reached, change to PRESENT.
                      - If stable free indications, change to ABSENT.
                  * PRESENT:
                      - Changes only allowed if allowed by Static Map Assumption (forbid PRESENT→ABSENT); in this design, no change is permitted.
                  * ABSENT:
                      - Similarly, no change to PRESENT unless overriding safety design; main spec forbids this.

                IR hysteresis:
                - Use K (K≥1, often equal to N) consecutive samples with same obstacle flag to change IR state; prevents flicker due to noise.

            </Content>
            <DerivedFrom>
                LL--MAP--1.2.3; LL--RELIAB--1.2.1; LL--RELIAB--1.2.2
            </DerivedFrom>
        </Data>
    </AdditionalData>
</Design>

